title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, margarine and Rice Krispies.
Batter will be stiff.
Roll by hand into small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Place on wax paper on a cookie sheet and chill.
While balls are chilling, melt together in top of double boiler the chocolate morsels and wax.
Dip each ball into chocolate mix and coat well.
Cool on wax paper (a toothpick works great to remove balls from chocolate).

title: quick batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cook in greased muffin tins at 375° until brown. Store unused portion of batter in refrigerator.
The batter keeps well for two weeks and can be prepared directly from the refrigerator; however, the batter will rise better if it is allowed to rise 30 to 60 minutes before baking.

title: easy dessert
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill 2 hours.

title: ms. read's sourdough starter
directions: In large glass jar or stone crock (may use gallon wide mouth jar), put water, sugar and yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add flour; stir well.
Cover; let stand in warm room for 36 to 48 hours, "stirring down" occasionally, if rising too much for the jar.
This is your starter.
When dipping into this jar, always do so with a clean spoon.
The mixture must remain only flour, sugar, water and yeast to keep without spoiling.
This Starter is ready for use, but always reserve some for future use.
The excess may be stored indefinitely in the refrigerator in a smaller jar.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook squash, onion, green and red peppers in melted butter over medium heat 7 to 9 minutes or until vegetables are slightly softened.
Thoroughly mix mayonnaise, cheese, egg, sauce and seasoning into vegetables.
Spoon into 2 1/2 quart baking dish, sprayed with nonstick coating.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned. Makes 8 servings.

title: russian strawberry soup
directions: If using fresh berries, hull, wash, drain and rub through a fine sieve.
Mix berries with sugar and sour cream.
Add cold water and wine.
Add lemon juice to taste to cut some of the sweetness.
Heat mixture very slowly over a low flame, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Do not allow the soup to boil. Serve either hot or cold.
When served cold, garnish each portion with a few whole berries.

title: oven-smoked turkey
directions: Wash turkey thoroughly.
Pat dry inside and out with paper towels.
Make paste of oil and salt.
Rub 1/4 cup of the mixture in cavities of turkey.
Place turkey on roaster rack.
Brush with plain oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix liquid smoke, pepper and vinegar into salt and oil paste.
Baste turkey every 20 or 30 minutes, more often, if needed.
Cook about 3 1/2 hours longer or until drumstick moves easily.
Do not cover turkey.

title: peanut patty
directions: Cook slowly until 250°.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 stick oleo, pinch of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet or in patties, then let dry.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening until light and fluffy; add eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Better with age.
Freezes well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook rotini according to package.
Brown beef.
Add sauce to meat and mix with cooked rotini.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Pour rest of mixture into dish and top with remaining cheese and your favorite pizza toppings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: stromboli roll
directions: Let bread rise as directed on package.
Cut each loaf in two. Roll each piece into a flat oblong, about 10 x 12 inches.
Layer, alternating meat and cheese, until all ingredients are used and all four pieces of bread are covered.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Tuck ends under.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix.
Just before serving add chopped tomato.

title: chicken las vegas
directions: Place ham on seasoned chicken with cheese in the center.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks, making sure the ends are sealed, too.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and water; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
together
eggs
and squash, then mash.
Add other ingredients.
Pour
ingredients into a greased casserole dish. Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: bacon
directions: I cook it and eat everything on it.
I eat whatever is cooked and I like what my mom fixes.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat loses its color.
Add salt and tomato sauce; cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes, until thickened.
Spread 1/2 green tomato slices on greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 of the cheese, then 1/2 ground beef mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chuckwagon supper
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef; drain and add other ingredients except topping.
Simmer while preparing topping.

title: colorful squash marinade
directions: Combine squash, zucchini, onions and red pepper; toss gently. Add garlic powder and pour Italian dressing over the vegetables. Refrigerate in a tightly covered container at least 8 hours or up to 2 days.
Stir occasionally.
Attractive served in a lettuce lined bowl.

title: goulash
directions: Brown onions and peppers in small amount of butter; remove from pan.
Brown meat seasoned with chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper in same skillet.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with part of meat; cover with macaroni.
Alternate layers of peppers and onions, corn, remaining meat, tomatoes and catsup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese is brown. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt one stick of oleo in iron skillet.
Add one chopped onion.
Add raw rice.
Cook until golden brown.
Add beef consomme and water.
Place in covered casserole and cook at 325° until liquid is absorbed (about 1 hour).

title: tri-level brownies
directions: Bottom Layer:
Stir together first 4 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in butter.
Pat in 11 x 7-inch or larger dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken into batter and fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add onion to broccoli and cook until done; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended. Add milk gradually and cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add broccoli and the remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serves 5.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Cook onions in bacon drippings or shortening until clear, about 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes or more.
Or place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: dairy noodle kugel
directions: Mix all ingredients, but milk and topping ingredients.
Grease and heat large roasting pan.
Pour in all ingredients, but milk and topping.
Pour milk over top.
Put topping on.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: fried chicken casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in margarine until tender. Add mushroom soup and pimento. Heat. Pour over chicken in casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: polenta
directions: Bring 5 cups of water to boil. Reduce to a simmer. Mix the cornmeal with 3 cups cold water. Stirring constantly, add cornmeal, cold water mixture and the salt to the simmering water. Stir until mixture thickens. Reduce heat and cook for approximately 10 to 15 minutes more. You may add your choice of fresh herbs or cheese. I prefer to add grated Parmesan. Grease a jelly roll pan. Spread mixture evenly. Let cool until firm.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Cut zucchini into bite- size chunks.
Peel and seed if old. Saute with large diced onions in small amount of butter until tender.
Add Parmesan cheese, croutons, salt, pepper and beaten egg with milk.
Stir until egg is set.
May add a little sherry or dry vermouth.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Using a pastry blender, mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and shortening to the consistency of cornstarch.
Pat into a greased 9-inch square pan, building up edges so it will contain peaches and topping.
Arrange drained peach halves on crust, dome up.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Remove from oven and add topping of sour cream and egg yolks, blended together.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt and oregano together.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Empty jars of artichokes with juice in a salad bowl; add drained beans and drained olives.
In a small pan, cook cleaned mushrooms in a water and vinegar solution (1/3 vinegar and 2/3 water).
When water boils, mushrooms are done.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Add mushrooms to rest of salad.
Mix and refrigerate.
May be prepared 1 or 2 days in advance.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Make usual salad of lettuce, tomato, green onion and cucumber.
Add sliced almonds and Ramen noodles cooked as follows: Break up noodles.
Cook with almonds and butter until slightly browned.
Add sesame seeds.
Cool.
Add to salad.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in pan over low heat, stirring until only sugar dissolves.
Cook until syrup forms a hard boil when dropped in cold water. Add a pinch of cream of tartar to egg whites, then beat until stiff.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites while beating with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture is thick enough to drop from spoon and will not run. Add nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: holiday shrimp dip
directions: Place can of soup in hot water for 30 minutes to thaw.
Using mixer gradually blend soup into cheese.
Heat mixture until smooth (overheating will make dip thin).
Add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with potato chips or corn chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: mexican chicken and chile casserole
directions: Wash chickens.
Bring broth to boil in large soup kettle.
Add chickens.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until drumsticks move easily. Lift chickens from broth and let cool.
Remove meat and discard bones and skin.
Cut meat into large strips.
Strain and chill broth, then lift off fat.
Cook broth uncovered over high heat until reduced to 1 cup.
Stir cornstarch paste into reduced broth. Cook, stirring, until very thick.
Set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until limp.
Add to thickened sauce along with chiles, garlic and Mexican seasoning.

title: december cider
directions: In a 4-quart kettle, combine apple juice, cranberry-apple juice and water. Stir in lemonade, nutmeg, cloves and 5 sticks cinnamon. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon before serving and discard. Stir in rum or Schnapps.
Pour into 12 (8 ounce) mugs or glasses. Serve warm with one of the remaining cinnamon sticks in each mug. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, milk, egg and oil together.
Put wieners on a stick and roll them in flour.
Dip them in cornmeal mixture and drop them in hot oil.
When they brown, take out and drain on paper towel.
Great for the grandkids!

title: dot's red hot apple pie
directions: Place 1 pie crust in pie pan.
Add apple pie mix in crust, sprinkle with flour, then cinnamon candy over the apples.
Place other crust over apple.
Crimp edges.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: microwave chili
directions: Brown and drain beef.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients.
Cook on High in microwave.
Cook 45 minutes, stir every 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes thick chunky chili.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and combine in a large bowl.
(I sliced pears and cut peach slices in two pieces.)
In a small bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk, sour cream and orange juice concentrate.
Beat with rotary beater until creamy. Fold into fruit mixture, adding grapes, if desired. Cover with additional mandarin orange sections, if desired.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix and milk together.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes. Take chocolate mix and add red food coloring.
Add to cake batter. Mix soda and vinegar together; fold into batter.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Melt bacon drippings or butter in saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper, Minute rice and hamburger.
Saute until lightly browned. Add tomato sauce and 2 cups hot water or add 4 cups canned tomatoes and omit the water.
Mix in salt and pepper and the mustard.
Bring to a boil quickly.
Then reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quiche for a crowd
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in preheated oven.
Blend together eggs, cottage cheese, salt, Tabasco and flour.
Pour into large bowl.
Add cheese, green chilies and margarine you melted in baking dish. Stir together by hand.
Pour into the 9 x 13-inch dish (now greased with butter or margarine).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Cool, then cut into appetizer squares.
Keeps 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.
Serve cold or reheated in microwave.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, then add sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat until it forms stiff peaks.
By hand, stir in saltines (crushed) and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. When cool, spread with a large container of Cool Whip.
Top with a can of cherry pie filling.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edges.
Cool in pan.

title: crescent beefy squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Stir in mushrooms and sour cream. Separate crescent dough.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides.
Pour on beef mixture. Top with cheese slices.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: fantastic casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook onions, celery and ground beef until the meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Spread soup over meat mixture.
Top with frozen potatoes. Bake at 400" about 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven about 5 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and almond.
Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into halves. Roll each half 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Cut into shapes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Makes 1 large casserole or 2 smaller ones.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package and drain.
Boil chicken breasts in water about 20 minutes.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange cooked chicken and broccoli on bottom. Combine soup and milk and pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine melted margarine and bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place juices and water in percolator. Place sugar and spices in basket and perk like coffee.

title: coconut cake(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs (one at a time) and 1/2 cup milk as you continue to cream.
Pulverize wafers, coconut and nuts together.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pound cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Mix flour and cocoa together.
Add flour and milk alternately; mix well.
Add pecans and vanilla; mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand in pan for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix cream, vanilla and eggs.
Then mix in flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger onion steak
directions: Melt enough butter
or oil in pan to cook onions, about 5 minutes.
Stir
in	cornstarch,
sauce,
bouillon and water. Cook until thick.
Form	hamburger
in
patties	and
cook
or broil. Pour onion gravy over and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini for 5 minutes and drain.
Melt margarine and combine with stuffing.
Layer 1/2 of the stuffing mixture in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Mix onion, celery soup, sour cream and carrots.
Put 1/2 of the zucchini on stuffing mix, then 1/2 of the onion mixture.
Repeat these layers.
Top with rest of the stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add in eggs, vinegar and food coloring.
Mix alternately dry ingredients with buttermilk into creamed mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean) at 375°.
Let cool and then top with vanilla icing.
Enjoy.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until heated.
Stir before serving.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, honey, salt and water for 5 minutes on high, then add peanuts and cook for 13 to 15 minutes until it registers 300° on a candy thermometer.
Stir in 1 tablespoon margarine, 1 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and crack.

title: pork chops with dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pork chops.
Spread on pork chops. Put
chops close together in pan.
Add enough water to cover bottom
of
pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting every 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Empty cake mix into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and drizzle all over cake and pat it down.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Spread on cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or less.
Cut when cool.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Lightly brush the bottom and sides of the pie shell with olive oil. Arrange the onion slices in an even layer in the bottom of the pie shell, packing them in tightly. Sprinkle the onions with basil. Arrange the tomato slices on top of the onions in a petal design. Lightly brush the tomatoes with the remaining olive oil. Stir mayonnaise and shredded cheese until well mixed, but not smooth. Spoon cheese mixture around the edge of the pie, just inside the fluted shell. Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking about 25 to 30 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown. Cool pie on a rack about 10 minutes before serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, margarine and sugar.
Press into cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice thin the potatoes. Saute onion in frying pan and 1 teaspoon of butter.
In saucepan, add milk, cheese, flour, salt, pepper and butter. Cook on slow fire until cheese melts. Add onion.
Layer potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour half the milk mixture over the potatoes. add remaining potatoes and milk mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In
a 4 quart saucepan, cook broccoli in a small amount of water
until
very
tender;
drain.
Add soup, milk, wine, butter and
pepper.
Stir
over
medium heat until bubbly and serve. Serves 8.

title: bannock bread
directions: Mix ingredients to form a dough.
Pinch or spoon an egg-size portion of the dough.
Flatten to a 1-inch patty on a flour-dusted plate.
Fry to a golden brown, turning once or twice.
Great with beef stew cooked over an open fire.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
In bowl, combine first six ingredients. Add next 3 ingredients, beating with mixer.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook green pepper, onion and garlic in shortening in covered skillet over low heat until tender.
Stir in soup, water, lemon juice, seasonings and shrimp.
Cook about 10 minutes; stir often. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tex mex cheese enchiladas
directions: You will need a 9 x 16-inch casserole pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Mix together chocolate, sugar and cornstarch.
Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: escarole soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil in large pot.
Make meatball mixture.
Your own meatballs.
Make small bite size meatballs. Heat olive oil in skillet and brown meatballs.
Drop meatballs in broth.
Cook chicken breast in microwave for a few minutes.
Cut into bite size and drop into soup.
Add garlic.
Rinse escarole well.
Cut escarole into 4-inch pieces.
When soup is boiling, add escarole.
Simmer about 2 hours.
About 15 minutes before you are ready to serve, add cheese.
Serve with cheese on table, Italian bread and butter.

title: linda's pound cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix all other ingredients.
Slowly stir liquid mixture into dry mixture.
Grease and flour fluted pan or sheet cake pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sunday night supper
directions: Mix flour and oil and gradually add milk to make a medium thick white sauce.
Add water to thin as needed.
Add salt, pepper, chicken and mixed vegetables.
Stir thoroughly but carefully. Remove from heat; cover and let stand as long as it takes to toast muffins.
Serve over muffins.
Great with fruit salad for a quick Sunday night supper.

title: lesueur salad
directions: In large salad bowl, alternate layers of lettuce, pepper, onion and celery.
Simmer frozen peas for approximately 5 minutes; drain and put over layers of other ingredients, alternating.
Seal airtight the entire mixture with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle tablespoon of sugar over mayonnaise.
Spread shredded cheese and bacon bits to taste as a topping.
Seal bowl tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach well.
Add all other ingredients.
Shape into balls (use teaspoon).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 100 balls.
Can be frozen before baking.
(Freeze on cookie sheet, then put in bag.)

title: light as a cloud peach dessert
directions: Trim crust from angel food cake and tear into bite size pieces.
Beat instant pudding mix with milk and stir in yogurt. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of the angel food pieces, then half of peach pie filling and half of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with sliced almonds.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Serves 12.
This is recommended for low cholesterol diets.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve warm or cold.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise, cheese and onion with broccoli.
Pour into buttered baking dish and toss crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix in apples.
Heap in pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with margarine. Adjust top crust; flute edges and cut vents.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix peeled, sliced apples, eggs, sugar and oil in bowl. Combine flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to apple mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill.
Best when chilled overnight.

title: chicken with garlic and oil
directions: Wash chicken well and pat dry.
Pour the olive oil into the bottom of a 14 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Dip chicken pieces in oil and turn to coat.
Turn chicken, skin side up and distribute evenly in pan.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch wedges. Arrange around chicken with onion and carrots.
Sprinkle garlic and lemon juice over all.
Salt and pepper over whole pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste every 15 minutes or so, until chicken is cooked and vegetables are tender.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Blend in lemon rind, lemon juice, sugar, flour and milk.
Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Pour into a pastry-lined pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a hot 450° oven; then reduce to a moderate 350° oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the edge comes out clean.

title: easter sweet bread(no yeast)
directions: Mix by hand the dry ingredients and shortening until it resembles cornmeal.
Add orange juice and lemon extract.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Pam spray 3 coffee cans and pour batter into each can, filling them halfway.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and remove from cans.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put boiling water, salt and Crisco in pan until Crisco melts. Take off of stove.
Add flour.
Put back on stove, stirring until mixture pulls away from pan.
Take off stove.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and the two egg whites.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes; reduce to 350°, bake 20 minutes more.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients in 4 parts.
Mix in oats, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes until cookies are golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen chewy cookies.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Remove skin.
In a large heavy skillet, brown chicken over medium heat with 2 tablespoons oil. Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle rosemary over chicken and add wine. Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator kuchen
directions: Scald milk. Stir in sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm.

Sprinkle yeast over warm water. Stir until dissolved. Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, egg and 2 cups flour with mixer until smooth. Stir in 2 additional cups flour with spoon to make a stiff batter (but not as stiff as bread dough).
Seal dough in airtight container and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Dough keeps for 3 days.
Shape dough and place in 4 greased pie pans.
Cover with topping and let rise until doubled in size.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and use crackers for coating.
Top with honey and cook in a baking dish with melted butter in bottom of pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients, stirring just until mixed.
Fold in cranberries.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage as you would to smother and cook in salted water until tender but still green.
Drain and reserve the liquid.
Cook ground beef with onions, garlic and other seasonings until brown. Mix cabbage with the meat, adding mushroom soup, green onions and cooked rice.
Before you think it is too dry, you can then add some of the liquid from the cooked cabbage.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with crumbs and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.
tags: amount of red hot pepper sauce

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: With rotary beater, beat eggs.
Add salad oil and sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick and foamy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and raisins.
Stir into zucchini mixture until just blended.
Divide batter equally into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire racks to cool.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and save juice.
Mix pineapple and marshmallows. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Mix the juice, flour, sugar, vinegar and egg together and cook until thickened. Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, mix all together with Cool Whip, apples and peanuts.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Pour water off salmon.
Debone fish.
Place skillet on setting of medium and add cooking oil.
Add fish and fry it for 1 minute. Add egg to dish and stir in until egg is cooked.
Dish is ready to serve.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Combine sour cream and sugar.
Heat over low heat until sugar melts.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 packages of thawed coconut.
Spread on cake and let cool.
Sprinkle other package of coconut on top of cake.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce, garlic, chili powder and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In casserole dish, layer 1/3 of chips, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 of the meat mixture, then 1/2 of the chips, 1 cup cheese and rest of meat mixture.
Then top with remaining chips and cheese.
Put in hot oven until cheese melts.

title: five hour oven stew
directions: Do not brown beef or drain tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients into 5-quart casserole and bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours. After 3 hours of cooking, stir well, then continue cooking remainder of the time. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken 'n' dressing bake
directions: Toss dressing in bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with broth, eggs and 1/2 can soup.
Place chicken over dressing.
Pour other 1/2 can soup mixed with milk.
Sprinkle pimento over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked carrots
directions: *About 2 pounds fresh carrots, cut up and cooked until tender and mashed thoroughly.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Combine mustard, chili powder, cayenne pepper and garlic powder; rub over ribs.
For sauce, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well and set aside.
Grill ribs, covered, over indirect heat and medium low coals for 1 hour or until tender, turning occasionally.
Baste with sauce during cooking, if desired.
Heat the remainder of the sauce, and serve with ribs.

title: fiesta mexichicken
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Bone and cut in large pieces.
Cut tortillas into 4 pieces.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa together.
Butter pan and add small amount of juice from chicken.
Place in layers tortillas, chicken and soup mixture, ending with soups.
Top with grated cheese.
Can be made ahead and let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour, with cover, at 300°.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Brush with melted butter and garlic while on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick of the butter with graham cracker crumbs.
Lay on the bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix rest of butter, confectioners sugar and eggs for 5 minutes, until smooth and creamy.
Spread over crumbs (carefully) and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: simple country coleslaw
directions: Whisk all ingredients, except cabbage and carrot, together in a large mixing bowl.
Add cabbage and carrot.
Toss well to coat. Refrigerate 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Mix both cheeses together thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cornstarch; mix well. Add vanilla and melted butter; mix in.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into 10-inch spring-form with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven during baking.
Shut off oven and leave in for 2 more hours.
You can top this with your favorite topping, thickened strawberries, etc.
It's great plain.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cook undrained pineapple, flour and sugar until thickened. Cool.
Slice bananas in pie shell.
Spread nuts on top.
Fill with cooled mixture.
Garnish with whipped cream, cherries and nuts.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil and saute onion, garlic and zucchini for a few minutes, then add the remaining ingredients.
Let cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender, stirring constantly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine yams, 1/2 cup sugar, coconut, egg, milk, 1/4 stick margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix until smooth and put in glass dish.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and flour and sprinkle over top.
Put 1/2 stick melted margarine over sugar and flour mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: In a medium bowl, blend soy sauce, seasoned rice, vinegar, 1 tablespoon oil, garlic powder and ginger. Add beef strips; toss well to coat. Cover and marinate for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: tortellini in broth
directions: For dough, combine eggs, egg whites, oil and 2 teaspoons salt in a bowl.
Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Turn dough onto a floured surface and knead in enough flour to make dough stiff. Wrap dough in waxed paper; set aside 10 minutes.

title: magic cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter in pan in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients (chips, the coconut, then chips, then nuts).
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool before cutting.

title: corny ham chowder
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain and reserve 1/4 grease.
Saute onions in bacon grease until tender.
Combine potatoes, celery, sauteed onions and broth in large saucepan. Bring mixture to boiling, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in ham and both cans corn.
Add half and half, heat thoroughly and season to taste.
Serve with crumbled bacon and parsley sprinkled on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandmother's bread and rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar; stir and set aside.
Dissolve shortening in boiling water in a large mixing bowl.
Add cold water and eggs.
Blend in salt and sugar and add yeast to this mixture.
Beat in 3 cups of flour until mixture is smooth.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft, workable dough.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add extracts one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Use 10-inch tube pan greased and floured.
(Bundt pan may be used.) Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 325° until done.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with remaining 3 ingredients.
Mix together. Refrigerate.

title: sunshine tarts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet (triangular mounds).

title: jean's chiquita's chicken
directions: Cook chicken about 45 minutes.
Cut chicken; add 1/2 cup water.
Saute the onion in the oil.
Add both cans of soup.
Then blend in the milk and cheese.
Heat until the cheese is melted. Add half cup broth and chilies, chopped with seeds removed. Always remember it is these chili seeds that clear your sinuses and set fire to your tonsils.
Cut tortillas into strips.
Layer on greased casserole dish.
Pour sauce on top.
Then layer of chicken.
Continue to layer tortillas, sauce and chicken until you run out of things to work with.

title: mini-donuts
directions: Roll the dough; make it a little flat on the bottom.
Put flour on top.
Roll it up again, even the bottom.
Make bottom flat again.
Put sprinkles on top.
Bake at 3 degrees for 1 hour. Then have yourself a mini-donut.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add to mixture of other ingredients and let simmer.

title: coffee punch
directions: Note:
For each 1 quart of coffee, use 1/2 pint of whipping cream.

title: chicken divan
directions: Bake chicken after sprinkling with salt and poultry seasoning. Cook broccoli until almost done; drain. Place in greased casserole. Chop chicken cross-grain. Place on top of broccoli. Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice in mixer. Add cheese. Pour over chicken. Stir crumbs in butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in large pan.
Cook until ball forms in cold water; take off heat.
Add last 3 ingredients; mix well. Pour in unbuttered pan.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain peas, green beans, corn and pimentos good.
Mix all together.
Add celery, carrot and onion.
After mixing all ingredients together, add Dressing.

title: sausage-beef casserole
directions: Brown smoked sausage and beef and place in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Cook onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon drippings until tender.
Add green bell peppers and cook 1 minute longer, stirring.
Add to meat in casserole.
Add beans and potatoes to casserole.
Sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly. Dissolve bouillon cubes and hot water.
Pour over casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: tangy fruit chops
directions: Brown chops in large nonstick skillet with 1/2 teaspoon vegetable oil.
Turn chops.
Stir in 1/2 cup of cranberry sauce, 1 tablespoon mustard and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Cover with lid. Simmer gently 5 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.
Serves 4.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, milk and salt; heat thoroughly.
Spread 1 1/2 cups potato chips in bottom of casserole.
Pour in chicken mixture.
Cover with remaining potato chips;
sprinkle with paprika and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead to blend.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 days.
Knead once each day.
On fourth day, divide into 5 sections.
Shape into sausage rolls.
Place the 5 rolls on broiler pan and bake at 140° for 10 hours.
Cool, wrap and refrigerate or freeze.

title: linguine with crabmeat
directions: Bring vegies and water to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Add milk, crabmeat, butter, garlic salt and basil.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in linguine and cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil or pressure cook chicken until tender; then cube.
Mix cubed chicken with sour cream and soup.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers (that have been mixed with melted margarine).
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake in 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In medium sized frying pan, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the parsley and onions.
Saute until onions are tender.
Add lemon juice and garlic; stir and continue to saute about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and hot sauce; stir and mix well. Saute until the shrimp are opaque and turn pinkish (about 5 minutes).
DO NOT OVERCOOK.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well. Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Cut up artichoke hearts into quarters.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Mix with sweet milk until batter is stiff.
With a teaspoon, drop into hot grease until brown.
Drain and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Place loaf into a casserole dish.
Brush top of loaf with extra catsup.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Place meat in medium size, heat-resistant, non-metallic mixing bowl.
Heat in microwave 6 minutes or until meat is browned; stir occasionally.
Drain excess fat off.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce to meat; stir to combine.
Heat in microwave 2 minutes.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Cook noodles 1/2 done; drain.
Lightly brown beef; add onion. Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add corn, soups, sour cream and pimento.
Season to taste.
Drain noodles and add to mixture. Cook 5 minutes.
Put into 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Mix all ingredients; add flour (13 to 14 cups) to make a medium dough.
Let set 1/2 hour; knead and let rise 1 hour. Shape; let rise.
Makes delicious caramel rolls.

title: fried carrots and apples
directions: Scrape carrots and cut lengthwise into thin slices.
Pare the apples, core and cut into slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Place a single layer of the apples and the carrots in a large skillet when the butter has melted. Cover tightly and cook until browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Just before cooking is finished sprinkle with sugar and salt.
Serve on a hot platter.

title: *christmas cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix other dry ingredients with flour.
Mix flour mixture and sugar mixture alternately with coffee.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter over low heat.
Stir in clams, juice and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Bring to boil; simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Pour over hot linguini and mix gently.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serve 4.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of about 12 muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan and roll muffins in 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine, then in mixture of 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.

title: country chicken(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat oil, lemon juice, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and garlic until mixed well but not frothy. Coat chicken with oil mixture.
Place chicken skin side down in a small heavy roasting pan.
Dot with oleo.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Gradually add milk; blend well.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Blend about 1/2 cup of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then add to the mixture in saucepan.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Cover and cool to lukewarm.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with the glaze.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning on medium speed.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, Cheddar cheese and green and red pepper.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with breadsticks.
Serves 10.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar; cream with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 30 seconds after each addition.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add brown sugar, oleo and eggs.
Last, stir in old-fashioned Quaker oats. Add chocolate chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Toss meat with 1 1/2 teaspoons soy sauce; set aside.
Combine broth with cornstarch and rest of soy sauce. Heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add meat and stir-fry.
Remove meat.
Add remaining oil and vegetables; stir-fry.
Add broth mixture to vegetables and boil. Add meat and nuts.
Heat 1 minute.
Add ginger.

title: granny jane's blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix as any other cake, saving 1/2 cup flour to dredge nuts and raisins in.
After you have mixed the batter, dredge the nuts and raisins.
Add to batter mixture, then add the jam.
Mix well. Pour into cake pans about 1/3 of an inch thick or thinner, if you can.
Bake until done.
Have syrup ready for icing.
Should be 7 to 9 layers.

title: fish dip
directions: Sift together flour, cornstarch, baking powder and soda.
Stir in water.
Beat egg white until frothy and smooth.
Cut fresh fish into chunks, dip and deep fry.

title: coffee cookies
directions: Combine and cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the beaten egg and mix well.
Combine sifted flour with spices, salt, baking soda and baking powder and mix well.
Add with coffee to rest of the batch.
Then add rest of the ingredients; add enough flour or water, if needed, to make right consistency for dropping.
Drop on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all of the	ingredients
together.	Put
pecans
in bottom of Bundt cake pan.	Pour batter over.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: company ham and noodles
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add ham; cook and stir until heated through.
Sprinkle with flour and stir for 1 minute. Reduce heat; gradually stir in sour cream.
Add the mushrooms. Cook and stir until thickened (about 2 to 3 minutes).
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: hawaiian coleslaw
directions: Slice luncheon meat into 8 crosswise slices, then cut each slice into 12 pieces.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1 tablespoon liquid.
In large bowl, toss luncheon meat with pineapple, cabbage and carrots.
In small bowl, blend mayonnaise, sour cream and reserved pineapple liquid. Add to meat and cabbage mixture, tossing until well mixed.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour, or until serving time.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries; pat dry with paper towel.
Combine sugar and milk; mixture will be stiff.
Take 1 teaspoon mixture in palm of hand and wrap around cherry.
Put on cookie sheet.
If sugar mixture becomes too dry, add a little hot water.
After all cherries are covered, put in refrigerator overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine
oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and zucchini (do not beat). Stir
in flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon (do not beat).
Add
pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in loaf pan.	Makes two.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt candy bars, syrup and 1 stick margarine over low heat. Cream 1 stick margarine, sugar, eggs, flour, salt, soda and buttermilk. Blend well and add butter and chocolate mixture to these ingredients. Add vanilla. Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Stir in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Cut with 2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place on ungreased pan.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 425°.

title: spring break key lime pie
directions: Blend egg yolks, condensed milk and Key lime juice until smooth. Pour into baked pie shell. Bake pie only 5 minutes at 350°. Chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: fudgy brownies with chocolate-orange glaze
directions: In a medium saucepan melt unsweetened chocolate with the margarine or butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs, orange peel and vanilla.
Using a wooden spoon, lightly beat the mixture just until combined.
Stir in the flour and nuts.
Spread the batter in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool the brownies in the pan on a wire rack.
Pour Chocolate-Orange Glaze over cooled brownies, spreading as necessary to glaze top evenly.
Let stand at room temperature until glaze is set.
Makes 9.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potato skins.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish. Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes for another 10 minutes until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside. Check with fork.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Combine brown sugar and flour in large bowl.
Stir in melted butter and blend until light and crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a tube pan.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat juices drained from fruit.
Add jello and dissolve. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Place all ingredients in non-aluminum pan. Stir and heat to boiling. Simmer for 1 hour. Serve hot. Makes 24 servings.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: With electric mixer, cream margarine, sugars, peanut butter and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture; stir until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: pecan delights a.k.a. mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and nuts gradually with vanilla. The mixture is very stiff.
Roll into little balls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ingredients for 1 hour, then put in jars and pressure at 10 pounds for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Rub chicken with garlic.
Sprinkle with salt.
Broil or grill chicken until cooked through (about 10 minutes).
Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Combine with honey, lime juice, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add a few pineapple slices.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease cake pan.
Sprinkle coconut on bottom of pan.
On top of coconut, add nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Put on top of nuts.
Mix butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Put on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen date-nut delight
directions: To eggs add flour, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in dates and pecans.
Spread in 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Crumble with fingers.
Put ice cream in bowl and stir in crumb mixture as soon as possible.
Pour in refrigerator tray or individual cupcake papers.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8 or makes 12 (2 1/2-inch) paper cup servings.

title: slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over cabbage and onions, let stand.
Bring vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add salad oil.
Bring to a boil again and pour over cabbage mixture.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Sprinkle half of mixture in pie shell.
Spread peaches over flour mixture. Sprinkle remaining flour mixture over peaches; top with butter slices.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until crust is brown and peaches are tender.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix cooking oil, milk and flour together.
Divide dough into fourths then roll each out to 7 by 5 inches until as thin as a pie crust.
Cut stick of butter long way in four strips.
Then sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar on each piece.
Roll up 4 times and pinch the ends together.
Bake at 300 degrees until golden brown.

title: jubilee cheese pie
directions: Turn cherry pie filling into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy. Reduce oven to 350°. Spoon cheese mixture over top of cherry pie filling. Bake 30 minutes. Cool. Spread sour cream over cooled pie.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and nuts.
With hands, press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 3 eggs, salt, cream cheese and confectioners sugar with mixer.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato kugel
directions: Melt butter to grease a shallow casserole dish.
Combine potatoes and eggs and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Mix flour in oil and brown until dark brown.
Stir constantly. Add onions and peppers and mix well until wilted.
Lower heat and add shrimp.
Do not stir too much.
Add 1 quart water and let it cook slowly, about 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer; put in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chop gumbo
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise into baking dish; cover with seasoned pork chops.
Slice onions and place on top of pork chops. Add 2 cans chicken gumbo soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots and cool.
Slice onion and green pepper and add to carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots. Marinate overnight or longer.
Drain and serve.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, eggs, parsley and salt; mix lightly.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in margarine; drain. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve the juice.
Combine pineapple, cheese and butter.
Mix sugar and flour; add pineapple juice.
Add to pineapple and cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Bake in 2-quart casserole dish for 20 minutes at 300°.
Add cracker crumbs; return to oven until crumbs are hot.

title: white chili
directions: Cook beans until tender. Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. In shallow bowl or bag, combine spices. Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes; toss in spice mixture to coat. Saut chicken in oil 2 minutes; add onion and garlic and cook until onion is translucent. Add to beans, along with broth and green chiles. Simmer for 1 hour. Tastes even better the next day.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and egg yolks.
Sift flour, then measure. Add dry ingredients together, then add to oil mixture.
Add hot water, pineapple juice and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°, until cake tests done.
A tube or Bundt pan is suggested.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger and use taco seasoning as directed. In a large bowl combine beans and picante sauce. In a 13 x 9-inch pan layer beans, hamburger, onion and cheese, then repeat again.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Shape into one inch balls. Roll balls in 1/4 cup sugar.
Place balls on greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Press Reese Cups on top of cookies while still hot.

title: hoisin-glazed chicken
directions: Preheat broiler for 5 minutes.
Mix garlic, ginger, hoisin sauce, chutney, vinegar, pepper and oil.
Remove skin from thighs or breasts.
If using chicken breasts, cut into strips.
Stir chicken into the marinade.
Sprinkle top of chicken with sesame seed.
Broil chicken 3 inches from broiler for 3 minutes.
Turn; sprinkle with more sesame seed and broil for 3 minutes.
Turn and broil 2 to 3 more minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Melt butter.
Grind cookies; reserve 1 cup.
Add melted butter to remaining cookies.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ice cream, then top with chocolate syrup.
Add Cool Whip; top with reserved cookies and, finally, the nuts.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook onions, peppers,
garlic
and
celery in margarine until tender.
Add 2
cans
soup,
parsley
and
shrimp;	mix gently. Stir in rice, bread crumbs and seasonings.	Pour into buttered casserole
and sprinkle Italian bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kate's party mix
directions: Mix cereals, pretzels and peanuts together. Mix salts and Worcestershire sauce into melted butter. Pour over cereal and mix well. Bake at 200° for 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes. Store in a tight container.

title: just the best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and blend.
Add oil, oats, cornflakes, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until mixed.
Will be very stiff after adding flour, soda and salt. Form in balls about the size of a walnut, press with fork and bake on ungreased cookie sheet about 12 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool for a few minutes before removing.

title: happy home
directions: These scriptures read daily and applied accordingly will supply a lot of spiritual uplifting not only in your heart, but those around you.
It is very low in calories and can be used everyday.

title: chocolate pretzels
directions: Combine and melt in double boiler over hot (not boiling) water all ingredients, except pretzels.
Remove from heat, but keep over hot water. Dip pretzels into chocolate mixture to coat thoroughly. Place on wire rack set over waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes or until coating sets. Remove and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or until surface dries.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cut the spareribs into 1-inch square pieces, then marinate with wine and soy sauce for 30 minutes.
Reserve soy sauce in bowl.
Deep-fry the spareribs for about 2 minutes, take out and heat oil again, then fry once more until spareribs turn very brown (about 1/2 minute).
Remove spareribs and drain off oil from frying pan.
Add sugar, vinegar, water and cornstarch, sesame oil and shredded green onion to the bowl, used for marinating spareribs.
This is the seasoning sauce.
Heat one tablespoon oil in frying pan, pour in the seasoning sauce, boil and stir until thickened and heated thoroughly.
Add spareribs and stir well before serving.

title: tangy cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Toss until well coated.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and oil. Add red food coloring and plum/tapioca baby food.
Add flour, cloves, cinnamon, soda, salt and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 70 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove.

title: delicious roast
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over roast and cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
This makes a delicious gravy.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Split wieners in half lengthwise but not completely through. Put cheese in middle of wiener; wrap with bacon piece and secure with toothpick.
Bake in 350° oven until bacon is done.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place chicken and vegetables in dish.
Stir together broth, soup and pepper; pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in baking dish. Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: special k fruit cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Blend sugar and butter together until fluffy.
Add eggs and fluff again.
Add vanilla, coconut, nuts, raisins and dry ingredients to butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in cereal.
Drop tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie(casserole)
directions: Mix together cooked spaghetti, butter, Parmesan, salt, pepper and egg.
Brown ground beef; drain and rinse.
Cook ground beef with onion, sugar, green pepper, oregano and garlic salt.
Cook until onion is soft.
Layer in casserole dish as follows: spaghetti mixture, cottage cheese, ground beef mixture and spaghetti sauce.
(Add Mozzarella cheese during last 10 minutes of baking time.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on back, except use buttermilk instead of water.
In a separate bowl, mix the package of cocoa and red food coloring.
Add to batter and beat for 2 minutes.
Add soda to vinegar, then fold this into batter (do not beat).
Bake according to box directions.
Test with toothpick.

title: raisin sauce for 100
directions: You take a large amount of laughter,

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2 baking dish. Bake at 350 for 20 - 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean and makes 6 servings.

title: chunky beef stew
directions: Cook beef in hot oil in a large Dutch oven until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except peas.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Stir in peas and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy whipped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
In 5-quart saucepot over high heat, heat potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, cream cheese, garlic salt, pepper, onion flakes and margarine or butter and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mash until smooth.
Gradually add heavy cream.
Heat in oven until hot.

title: minty garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prick potatoes with a fork and bake on a cookie sheet for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove potatoes from oven, cut in quarters and place in bowl.
While hot, toss with oil, salt, pepper and garlic.
Gently toss in chopped mint.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt
chocolate with margarine over low heat; stir until blended.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt;
beat
in
vanilla and eggs.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie
shell.
Mix coconut and pecans and sprinkle over filling.
Bake at
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 4 hours.
If topping browns too quickly, cover with aluminum foil during last 15 minutes.

title: granola cereal
directions: Melt margarine in a large cookie sheet with sides.
Mix the next 3 ingredients thoroughly, then spread evenly on top of margarine.
Bake at 200° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Drizzle honey over cereal before baking the last 15 minutes.

title: cheesy lasagna pizza
directions: Grease a 14-inch pizza pan or 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Brown ground beef; drain the fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1/4 cup water and spaghetti sauce seasoning mix (reserve 1 tablespoon of seasoning mix for the crust); simmer while preparing crust.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Separate biscuits.
Flatten and press into bottom and up sides of a greased muffin tin.
In skillet, brown beef and drain off grease.
In a small bowl, mix ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder.
Stir until smooth.
Add to browned meat and mix well.
Divide meat mixture among biscuit-lined muffin cups, using about 1/4 cup in each.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from tin and serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add milk and butter.
Stir constantly.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, coconut and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chicken pepper pot soup
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter until brown.
Stir in soup, water, chicken and curry.
Heat and serve.

title: sausage and rice royal
directions: Fry sausage in skillet until lightly browned.
Drain sausage on paper towels.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in the drippings until wilted.
Add water and salt.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add sausage and uncooked rice. Pour all into a greased casserole.
Put lid on; cook for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mound cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Bake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix sugar, milk and marshmallows; cook until marshmallows melt, then add coconut. Spread over cake while cake is still warm. Spread frosting over top of coconut mixture. Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Set aside.
Cook chicken well done; cool and pull into small pieces.
Mix chicken with mushroom soup, noodles and salt.
Stir well.
Spray ovenproof dish with Pam.
Sprinkle bottom of dish with 1 cup cracker crumbs. Pour chicken mixture over crackers evenly, then sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until heated and top gets lightly brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly with whisk.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°; bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 45 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream. Refrigerate any leftovers immediately.

title: cheese bacon strips
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, bacon (broken in small pieces), egg, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and hot sauce together.
Spread mixture on toasted bread and cut each slice into 4 strips.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Wrap in foil and refrigerate 2 hours.
Remove and make logs or balls. Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cheese rarebit broil
directions: Combine soup and milk and simmer.
Add Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Place toast in baking dish.
On each slice, put bacon, tomato slices and mushroom bits.
Pour cheese on top and broil until crusty.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Soak onion in wine for at least 1 hour.
Mix together all ingredients.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: new york style cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs and sugar; add melted butter and combine thoroughly.
Press into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: greek shrimp
directions: Cook pasta, drain and set aside.
Keep warm.

Saute shrimp and red pepper flakes in 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet for 1 to 2 minutes or until shrimp are slightly pink. Arrange shrimp in a baking dish and sprinkle with Feta cheese; set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Follow directions for cookie dough.
Press into bread pan or 13 x 9-inch pan for crust and bake.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on crust.
Arrange drained fruit in layers. Sprinkle with coconut.
Heat preserves (makes it easier to spread) and pour over fruit.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: wassail(1 quart)
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups boiling water and boil 5 minutes. Add spices.
Cover and allow to stand for 1 hour.
Add remaining water and fruit juices and mix well.
Strain.
Heat to boiling and serve.

title: caramel cake
directions: Melt the butter, caramels and milk in a double boiler, then cool.
Mix cake as directed.
Put half in cake pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put the caramel mixture over the cake.
Put the rest of the cake mix on top of the caramel.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes more or until done in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheddar bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, mix cheese, mayonnaise, onions and chili powder; stir until well mixed.
Spread each half of bread with cheese mixture within 1/2-inch of the edges.
Arrange olive slices over cheese.
Wrap each bread half in foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 12 servings.

title: one pot meal
directions: Put Polish sausage in pot, then potatoes and the cabbage. Boil until cabbage and potatoes are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti and tomatoes au gratin
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
Saute chopped onion in margarine until transparent.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice to dissolve cornstarch.
Mash tomatoes.
Combine with salt, sugar and pepper.
Bring to boil in a saucepan.
Dissolve cornstarch in reserved tomato juice.
Add to boiling tomatoes, stirring constantly.
Stir until tomatoes thicken and raw starch taste has disappeared.
Add onion and spaghetti to tomatoes.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Grind or put through blender the hot peppers (wear rubber gloves).
Mix all ingredients except brown sugar and flour.
Cook together 30 minutes.
Add sugar and flour in a paste for the last 5 minutes.
Cook to desired thickness.
Put in jars and seal. Boil in jars 5 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl with 2 to 3 cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Place in greased 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: baked chicken breast, back and dressing
directions: Select whole chicken (about 3 pounds) with enough skin to seal rear body cavity. Remove legs, thighs and wings, leaving back, breast and rib cage attached. Rinse and pat dry. Rub with a little cooking oil. Sprinkle with ground thyme, salt and pepper inside and outside. Stuff cavity with your favorite moist dressing and seal cavity with skewers. Bake at 400° in shallow baking pan. Turn often with tongs until chicken
has browned and back bones begin to caramelize. Dressing should be steaming hot. Cover with loose foil if browning occurs too quickly. Serves 4.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet cook beef, peppers, onions and garlic until beef is browned and vegetables are tender. Add remaining
ingredients, bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: melbadene and sandra's punch
directions: Mix real good and put in freezer and freeze.
Then next morning, take out of freezer and when you can, cut up ice into slush.
Most people like it slushy.

title: knorr vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with vegetables and crackers.

title: peanutty pretzels
directions: Melt bark; add rest of ingredients and drop on wax paper. Let harden.
These freeze well, also.

title: chicken breasts deluxe
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with dried beef.
Roll each deboned chicken breast in a slice of bacon.
Place on chipped beef. Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 275°. The last few minutes, turn oven to broil.
Watch!
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
(This is my family favorite on Christmas Eve.)

title: spice drop cookies
directions: Combine dry
ingredients
to creamed ingredients.
Then add 2/3 cup seedless
raisins and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on
greased
cookie
sheet.
Allow
space between cookies as they triple in size.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: goulash slop
directions: Dice up your leftover meat.
Add your leftover or fresh vegetables and spices with your quart of tomatoes.
Let simmer. Boil your rice or macaroni and add all together.
Season to taste.

title: raisin pie
directions: Add raisins to boiling water; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into hot raisins.
Bring to full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in peel and juice. Pour into pie crust and dot with butter.
Adjust top crust; cut and vent.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.
Good Luck.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll on floured board 1/8-inch thick.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute onions, peppers, celery and green onions in margarine until soft.
Add flour, parsley, crawfish or shrimp; cook for 15 minutes.
Add jalapeno relish (if you like it hot), Velveeta cheese, half and half and garlic.
Cook 15 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender; rinse noodles in cold water again and fold noodles in sauce.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes large recipe.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand and real lime.
Pour into prepared pastry shell. Bake at least 30 minutes; cool.
Chill, then top with whipped cream (yellow food coloring may be added for color).

title: shrimp and crab quiche
directions: Sprinkle crab meat, shrimp, cheese and onion in pie shell. Beat eggs slightly and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie crust.
Cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce temperature to 300° and cook for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Allow to cool at least 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento and half of the crushed Cheez-Its crackers.
Pour into a shallow casserole.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon party log
directions: Remove salmon skin and bones, then flake.
Combine salmon with all ingredients except parsley.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Shape into an 8 x 2-inch log.
Roll in parsley.
Makes 16 (1/2-inch) servings.
Each equals 1 P and 40 opt. cal.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes firm but not dry.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Mix in pie filling and crushed pineapple. Mix well. Refrigerate until set. Blend together cream cheese, sugar and sour cream together. Spread evenly over Jell-O mixture. Sprinkle with nuts and chill.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Shape meat into 3 or 4 patties.
Place on foil.
Top with vegetables.
Wrap tightly.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Butter and season.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pork chops.
Brown chops in frying pan.
Put in baking dish with mixed ingredients.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mock thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all in dressing jar.
Serve over green salad.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until almost tender.
Saute sausage and onion in margarine.
Drain potatoes and combine with sausage and onion. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cornish game hens with sweet potato-maple-pecan stuffing
directions: Remove giblets from game hens; wash and dry.
Season inside and out with salt and pepper (or lemon pepper) to taste.
Bake (or microwave) sweet potatoes.
Scoop out the flesh and mash.
Melt butter or margarine; add maple syrup.
Stir into sweet potatoes. Add pecans.
Stuff game hens.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Extra stuffing may be warmed in a small casserole dish.

title: strawberry-banana dessert
directions: The night before, in a large glass bowl or 9 x 13-inch glass pan, make jello.
When partially thickened, add thawed frozen strawberries.
Let set until next day.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt
caramels
in water in top of double boiler.
When melted,
add
the pecans and stir well.
Remove from stove and drop
by
teaspoonful
onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm enough
to remove from paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler, then dip caramels into chocolate mixture with
a fork.
Place on waxed paper until firm.
Will freeze and store well.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 4 ounces cheese and cooked bacon or ham into pie pan; shape around sides.
Beat eggs, onion, flour, melted margarine, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; 40 minutes in glass pan.

title: linda's light pancakes
directions: *To Make Sour Milk:
Place one tablespoon vinegar in a 2 cup measuring glass.
Add enough fresh milk (either 2%, 1% or skim milk) to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Stir well and let mixture stand about 5 minutes before using in recipe.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and serve cold.

title: tomato avocado dip
directions: Press avocados through a coarse sieve.
Add lemon juice and vinegar at once.
Then add tomato and blend.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover tightly and chill.
Serve as a dip with vegetable sticks.
Makes 3 cups.
Note:
Mixture darkens when left uncovered for long periods.

title: texas taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add taco mix as directed.
Set aside to cool.
Have salad ingredients chopped and ready.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and store overnight in refrigerator.
For veggies, crackers or chips.

title: noami's prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add remaining ingredients. Bake in 8 x 12 Pyrex at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cup cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Mix well the cream cheese, egg, sugar and peanut butter cups; drop by teaspoon and spread on cake before baking.

title: outstanding punch
directions: Chill the juices and ginger ale.
Just before serving, combine juices in a punch bowl.
Stir in the ginger ale.
Yield: 4 1/2 quarts.

title: quick fruit crunch
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of medium size cake pan.
Put cake mix on top, then melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: four cheese lasagna
directions: Sauce: Clarify onion in 2 to 3 tablespoons olive oil. Add crushed garlic and simmer another 3 minutes.

Add 16 ounces tomato sauce and tomato paste. Mix well. Add another 16 ounces tomato sauce and stir. Add 2 handfuls crushed fresh dried basil (3 approximately 3 tablespoons), 2 smaller handfuls of fresh dried oregano (approximately 2 tablespoons) and 2 bay leaves. Stir in herbs. Add 1/8 cup red wine and 3 tablespoons brown sugar. Stir. Simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Oven 400 degrees.
Mix ingredients and put in oven safe dish. Mix crust ingredients in separate bowl and pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jam boats
directions: Combine walnuts and sugar.
