Add egg whites gradually until mixture forms a thick paste. Drop in large balls onto a baking sheet coated with nonstick vegetable spray. With the back of a spoon, make a hollow in the center of each ball.
Bake for 20 minutes in on oven which has been preheated to 300°.
Remove when lightly brown.
Place warm jam in the hollow of each cookie and serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add spices.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on bun, open faced.
Great tasting.
Kids love it too!

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Mix oatmeal and flour on a sheet of wax paper.
Stir sugar, butter and milk in a small saucepan over low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat; stir in oats, flour and vanilla.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: norwegian meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, pepper, ginger, nutmeg and cornstarch. Put in milk and mix well.
Make into balls and roll in flour.
Fry in oleo until nice and brown.
Add water and cook for 45 minutes. Add onion when you add water and bouillon cube to make gravy.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Put jello, water and strawberries in bowl; stir until strawberries are thawed and jello begins to thicken.
Add pineapple.
Pour half in dish.
Spread Dream Whip on first mixture.
Add rest of jello mixture and chill.
Best to prepare the day before needed and chill overnight.

title: pickled slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, salad oil, and sugar.
Add salt. Mix cabbage, celery seed, mustard, and onion.
Pour cooked mixture over other ingredients.
Put in jar and refrigerate.

title: punch(serves 70 punch cups)
directions: Combine juices and sugar; chill.
Pour juice mixture and ginger ale over ice in punch bowl.
Add mint leaves and serve.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes (covered).
Stir occasionally.
Cut zucchini and add tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: pineapple rum torte
directions: Combine and mix first 4 ingredients until crumbs are formed; then work with hands, until it is soft dough.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with 1/2 inch extending up sides.
Prick bottom and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust begins to form.

title: savory pork and apple stir-fry
directions: Prepare rice pilaf as package directs, substituting 1 cup water and 1 cup apple juice for water.
Cut meat into 1 1/2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Toss with combined seasonings.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute meat 3 to 4 minutes until no longer pink.
Add apples and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until apples are almost tender.
Add combined 1/3 cup apple juice and cornstarch.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes until thickened to form glaze. Stir in nuts.
Top rice with pork or chicken mixture.

title: mammy's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend well.
Chop nuts and mix in part of flour.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder; fold into egg butter mixture.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix by hand.
Put in greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake for 3 hours at 275°.
If you use small pans, cut baking time.
Doubles well.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Melt bouillon cube in boiling water.
Mix all wet ingredients together.
Put roast in large pot and cover with onions.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce mixture over and cover with lid.
Bake at 300° for 6 to 7 hours.
When done, pull apart with long fork.

title: skid row stroganoff
directions: Brown garlic, onion and beef in oil.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms.
Stir and cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: dutchie
directions: Cook ground beef in a little oil 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown or cook into lumps.
Add sauce, etc. and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Cool quickly.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix half the coconut with other ingredients and sprinkle rest on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Crust: Grease and flour 13 x 9 pan. Combine yellow cake mix, less 1 cup, 1/2 cup butter and 1 egg. Press into pan.

title: chicken celebre
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish and cover with mushrooms. Break up bay leaves and sprinkle over chicken.
Arrange the quartered tomatoes and green peppers over the chicken.

title: tomato and cucumber salad(russia)
directions: Mix the tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and dill together, add salt and pepper. Stir in enough sour cream to make a creamy dressing, it doesn't take much.

title: brickle bars
directions: Melt the butter and baking chocolate in a saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and add the sugar, eggs and vanilla. Lightly beat the mixture and stir in flour.
Spread the batter in a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with almond brickle and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack; cut into pieces and enjoy.

title: strawberries amaretto
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Serve over strawberries already flavored with powdered sugar and Amaretto.

title: honey apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl cream eggs, oil, sugar and honey together.
In separate bowl sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Combine the two mixtures.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Spoon into large baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: candied cranberries
directions: In a saucepan, combine the 2 1/2 cups sugar and the water; bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Place cranberries in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour boiling syrup over cranberries. Bake in 300° oven, uncovered, for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cover loosely and store overnight.

title: pineapple sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter and sugar in a square pan. Add pineapple and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Place biscuits on top. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: trees and raisins
directions: Cut broccoli into small heads (trees). Combine with bacon pieces, raisins and onions in large bowl. In separate bowl, blend the mayo, sugar and vinegar. Pour over broccoli mixture; stir to coat well. Cover and marinate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch pan.
Combine oats, sugar, margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Firmly press mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 18 minutes or until mixture is brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over toffee.
Let stand 10 minutes; spread chocolate evenly over toffee.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool completely; cut into squares.
Store tightly in cool, dry place. Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard ball.
Add peanuts and oleo.
Cook to light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Stir.
Pour onto 2 greased cookie sheets.
As it cools, stretch out.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and cream in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients. Put half
of the crumb mix in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chips over mix.
Let melt. Cool.
Put caramel mix over.
Put remaining crumb mix over caramel mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: wash day cobbler
directions: In a medium saucepan heat fruit and cinnamon until boiling. Set aside.
In a medium mixing bowl combine flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in a quart casserole.
Pour in batter.
Add hot fruit.
Sprinkle the remaining 3/4 cup sugar over entire cobbler.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 or 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs, one at the time.
Add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Cover with chocolate Cool Whip.
Chill.
Very good.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; fit into cookie sheet(s).
Pinch "seams" together.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Cool.

title: easy elephant ears
directions: Roll biscuits extra thin.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Coat biscuits with cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: quick cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; cook raisins and water together in a right high pan.
Add margarine and soda to hot mixture until margarine melts.
Take off stove.
Add dry ingredients to pan, stirring, then add beaten egg.
Mix until well blended.
Spread in greased large cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, spread with butter and powdered sugar.

title: microwave rhubarb sauce
directions: Place rhubarb and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover. Microwave 10 minutes on High or until rhubarb is tender, stirring well after 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Adjust sugar to taste.
Cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream until fluffy. Blend in well beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Blend in prunes.
Bake in well-greased and floured pans (three 8-inch pans or two 9-inch pans, 1 1/4-inch deep).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza cups (mini)
directions: Brown and drain beef; stir in tomato paste, onion and seasoning (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together making a thin batter.
Fry in pan like pancakes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend together milk, lemon juice, grated lemon rind or lemon extract and egg yolks.
Pour into chilled crust or cooked pastry shell.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until almost stiff enough to peak.
Put in sugar gradually, beating until stiff but not dry.
Pile lightly on pie filling.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Let simmer slowly for about 30 minutes. Add seasoning to taste. Stir often. Cover and let simmer on medium. Serve hot with crackers.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover top with bread crumbs and pour another stick of melted oleo over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serves about 30 people.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend by hand powdered sugar, flour and butter.
Press into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon juice.
Pour over crust. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: baked ham
directions: Cover ham with mixture of the cider, brown sugar, mustard and salt.
Insert cloves in top.
Bake as directed.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chocolate chips and wax and press into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Remove from freezer and cut into squares.
Use double boiler and dissolve chocolate chips and wax.
Dip pieces and lay on waxed paper until cooled.

title: honey date muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper-line 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
In a medium bowl, combine cereal, milk, honey, oil and egg. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir to break up cereal.
Add flour, dates and baking powder, stirring just until moistened.
Divide evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix
and chill.
Before serving, slice 2 or 3 fresh and firm bananas into salad; mix and serve.

title: forgotten chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, chicken soup and curry powder and put into a greased casserole dish.
Place mushrooms on top, then chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Put tight cover on and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: dogs in a blanket
directions: You will also need 10 toothpicks.

title: red wine sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Slice lemons, limes and oranges; add just prior to serving.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolk.
Add sugar, salt and milk; strain.
Add egg white, stiffly beaten.
Add pinch of nutmeg.
Serve cold.
If desired, 1 teaspoon cocoa can be added to mixture.

title: cream cheese and chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Place in a casserole and refrigerate.
To serve, top with pecans which have been sauteed in butter.
Heat at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Serve with crackers.
Can be doubled.

title: great baked beans
directions: Fry the bacon.
Cook the onions in the bacon grease and discard the grease.
Put all ingredients together; top with bacon. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: perdernales river chili
directions: Sear meat with onion and garlic in Dutch oven until light colored, stirring constantly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then on low heat, simmer slowly about 1 hour, stirring now and then.
Keep floating fat skimmed off.

title: franks and chili manicotti ole
directions: Cook manicotti in boiling, salted water as per directions on package; set aside.
Shred 2/3 of cheese and set aside.
Cut remaining cheese into 4-inch strips.
Slit franks lengthwise and insert strip of cheese in each.
Place stuffed frank inside each cooked manicotti.
Combine beans, tomatoes and peppers.
Spoon 2 cups of mixture in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remainder of mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: wild rice and shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickles, pickles, pickles
directions: How many times you have wanted a "specific" pickle to eat. Well, stock up; be creative; and go for it.

title: simply sensational herbed nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients until pecans are coated.
Place nuts on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Yields 4 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix and bake in
tube
or
Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour. Then glaze.

title: rich squash delight
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread uncooked rice around in dish.
Spread squash in a layer over rice.
Sprinkle onion over squash.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix water with soup and pour over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
For last 10 minutes of baking, top with grated cheese and allow to melt.

title: soup stock basics
directions: Basic Information: Simmer meat or vegetables in water or wine. While ingredients must be of good quality, consider using poultry carcasses, leftover vegetables and gravies from dinner, cooking water from potatoes, or the peelings or leaves left after preparing fresh vegetables. Refrigerate peelings until ready to use.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Pit cherries and place in mixing bowl.
Combine cornstarch and sugar; add the cherries along with the "Kirsch" or "almond" flavoring.
Let mixture stand about 15 minutes before putting into pie shell.
Prepare your favorite recipe for pie crust and fit the bottom crust in pan.
Stir the cherry mixture gently and pour into shell.
Dot the fruit with 1 or 2 tablespoons butter.
Place lattice strips on pie.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: party potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes. Do not peel. Cut potatoes in large pieces and deep fry. Drain on paper towel.
Place in casserole dish. Cover with Ranch dressing. Sprinkle cheese over top and place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: taco salad
directions: Arrange lettuce on plate, then make a little cup with the corn chips (to hold the chili) in the center of the lettuce. Scatter tomatoes all around the lettuce.
Scoop the chili on the chips. Sprinkle grated cheese over whole salad. Top it off with sour cream.
Put on your favorite dressing (we use Ranch) and chow down!

title: pear pie
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan. Top with pears. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix well and pour over fruit. Sprinkle a little sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit roll up
directions: Select a ripe or slightly overripe fruit.
Sort and wash. Remove blemishes.
Peel, pit, hull, seed and core fruit as necessary.
Cut fruit in pieces; place in blender.
Add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice per 2 cups of fruit to prevent browning. Blend until smooth.
If the puree is tart, add 1 tablespoon sugar, corn syrup or honey for each 2 cups of fruit.
Most fruits do not need added sugar.
Heat oven to 140°.
Line a cookie sheet with plastic wrap or spray with a vegetable spray.
Do not use waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Spread the puree on plastic wrapped cookie sheet.
Tilt the cookie sheet back and forth to smooth out any ripples.
Place the cookie sheet in oven.
Leave the door slightly open (approximately 2 to 6 inches, depending on oven door) to allow humid air to escape.
To test for dryness, loosen edge of the leather from the cookie sheet and lift as if to peel back.
Properly dried leather is slightly sticky to the touch.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops first.
Put onion, green pepper, tomato and rice on each chop.
Pour 2 1/2 cups bouillon, seasoned with salt, pepper and thyme, over it.
Bake, covered, at 325° to 350° for 50 minutes or may use electric frypan.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Garnish with sliced fruit.

title: pizzasagna
directions: Brown sausage in saucepan.
Drain.
Add pepperoni and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In casserole dish layer 1/3 pasta, then 1/3 sauce and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, then remove, cover and bake 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fair corn dogs
directions: Combine the 3 dry ingredients and then add in the last 2 ingredients; mix well. Dip hot dogs into mixture until they are fully covered. Drop corn dogs into deep-fryer and cook for about 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 1-gallon ice cream freezer.
Finish filling freezer with milk.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Put in airtight jars.

title: beef dumpling soup
directions: Boil all together until tender.

title: peanut butter 'n chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat Parkay Spread sticks, sugars and peanut butter in large bowl with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix and roll into meat balls.
Heat 3 tablespoons roux, add 2/3 cup water and simmer.
Add meat balls and parsley.
When cooked, serve on hot rice.

title: chile pepper cheese roll
directions: Roll out Velveeta with rolling pin between waxed paper (about 15 x 18-inch).
Spread with cream cheese and chopped green chilies.
Roll up like a jelly roll, about the size of a round cracker.
Chill 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and ginger ale in heavy pan; cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Add gelatin and red food coloring.
Let cool.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: amy's chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt & cinnamon.
In separate bowl, cream butter and sugar.
In another bowl, mix eggs, zucchini, vanilla, nuts and milk.
Alternately combine wet & dry ingredients into butter/sugar mixture.
Spread into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Mix together cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted oleo and cover potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scotch broth
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large pot and bring to a boil. Lower heat and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes. Serve with fresh rye bread and butter.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese in bowl 30 to 45 seconds or until softened; beat until smooth.
Mix with 2/3 cup picante (maybe less, 1/2 cup).
Spread evenly over bottom of serving plate.
Sprinkle evenly with lettuce, tomato, cheese and olives.
Drizzle on last of picante, if desired.
It may be hot!
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.

title: quick tamale bake
directions: Heat fat in skillet.
Add onion and seasonings.
Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Add corn and tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Stir up the corn muffin mix and spoon over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Take egg yolks and beat until very light.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Combine flour and salt.
Add with milk to mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Cook over medium heat 1 to 1 1/2 cups of batter for 30 to 45 seconds on first side.
Turn and bake until steam stops or until golden brown.

title: rotel tomato chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts; remove from broth and boil noodles.
If any broth is left when noodles are done, drain.

title: peanut butter crunch snack
directions: Heat oven to 250°, heat peanut butter, dry milk and butter in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2 inches. in oven until butter is melted.
Stir until blended.
Stir in cereal and peanuts until coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Spread on paper towels, waxed paper or aluminum foil to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: sadie hobb's brownstone front cake
directions: Combine and mix first 4 ingredients in order given.
Cook slowly until thick; cool.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add well the beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add cooled chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
This makes a 3 layer cake.

title: granny's ham and cheese potato casserole
directions: Granny always used her leftover ham.
Ham should be cut into chunks.
Peel and dice potatoes.
You can boil potatoes before putting casserole together.
Place butter in microwave-safe dish and cook on High until melted.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Whisk in milk and pepper, blending well.
Cook on High 3 minutes stirring once.
Whisk until smooth.
Layer with ham, potatoes, mixture and cheese.
Continue doing this until you have used all of your ham and potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375 ° until bubbly or potatoes are done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix all liquid ingredients in small bowl, then add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator, covered. To cook:
On floured wax paper take out amount needed. Mix with flour and pinch off into biscuits and place on greased pan. Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Blend with 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Add remaining water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat, add lemon juice, a little grated rind and butter.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Chop celery.
Drain broth from chicken and add water to make 6 cups.
Put celery, broth-water mixture and bouillon cubes into large pan.
Heat to boiling about 10 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cover and boil gently for about 10 minutes, until noodles are tender. Add chicken, salt and pepper; heat to boiling.
Serves 6 (1 cup each).

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir in 1 can of French fried onion rings (or can use 1/2 cup of chopped onion).
Return to oven and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Saute carrots and leeks in butter for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add flour and stir.
Pour in chicken broth, sugar, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly and put through blender.
Add cream to mixture and liquefy.
Serve warm or chill before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "great with steak" potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients in container with tight-fitting lid. Shake potatoes in mixture and place skin down on pan. Pour remaining ingredients over potatoes after all have been coated. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 375° oven 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix salt, Accent and oil.
Pour over vermicelli and mix well. Let marinate overnight.
Cut up next 7 ingredients and pour over the vermicelli the next day.
Mix well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together the above and put in casserole.
Crush 8 or 10 crackers; add to crackers a little of the cheese or dot with butter and put over top of corn.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. You can omit green beans, but add a second can of corn.

title: vermicelli with zucchini
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until lightly brown; add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add water and bring to boil.
Add zucchini and basil and cook 10 minutes.
Add vermicelli and cook on low heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; add beef and next 4 ingredients. Cook only until meat turns very light brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain off any excess fat.
Stir in water, Worcestershire sauce and catsup; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes or until desired consistency is obtained. Serve in heated sandwich buns.
This recipe makes 10 servings.

title: aunt mary's spareribs
directions: Place spareribs on rack in roasting pan.
Combine all ingredients for sauce.
Brush spareribs with half of sauce.
Bake ribs in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Brush with remaining sauce a few times.
Let ribs rest for a few minutes, then serve.

title: marinated summer squash
directions: Arrange vegetables in layers in a container.
Thoroughly mix ingredients for marinade and pour over vegetables.
Chill.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Melt butter slowly over low heat.
Have eggs beaten slightly. Add the melted butter slowly.
Add the other ingredients, then pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese-filled manicotti
directions: Prepare and drain pasta.
Rinse with cold water, drain and arrange in a single layer.
Mix Ricotta cheese, 1 1/2 cups of Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Using at least 1/3 cup per shell, spoon mixture into manicotti shells.
Place filled shells in single layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over manicotti shells.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and drain.
Mash potatoes; add salt, pepper, milk and butter together.
Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla, flour and salt. Spread on 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Melt chocolate; spread on bars.
Sprinkle on nuts.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together Veg-All, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and chestnuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: dutch ginger cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add sugar and chopped ginger. Melt butter and allow to cool slightly.
Mix egg into butter, reserving 1 teaspoon of egg for glazing.
Add butter to flour and mix well.
Press mixture into a greased 8-inch sandwich tin (round).
Brush top with reserved egg.
Arrange almonds decoratively on top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until cake is golden and firm to touch.
Allow to cool in tin; turn out and cut into wedges and serve.

title: grandma's ginger creams
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add egg; mix.
Add molasses and mix well.
Sift flour and add slowly, mixing in well.
Add spices, salt and soda.
Add water a little at a time; mix well.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoon and bake 8 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Frost with a thin powdered sugar icing, if desired.

title: soda pop cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and salt. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately with 1 cup strawberry pop to creamed mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake 25 to 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cook onion in water until soft; drain water from onions.
Cook sugar, spices and vinegar, then add onions and cucumbers.
Cook until they change color.
Bottle hot.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; set aside.
In big bowl, combine soy sauce and bouillon cube, dissolved in small amount hot water, ginger and garlic powder.

title: snappy turtle cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend butter and sugar thoroughly; add egg and egg yolk and beat well.
Blend in flavorings.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly. Arrange split pecan halves (rounded side up) in groups of three on greased cookie sheets to resemble head and legs of a turtle.
Mold dough into balls.
Dip bottom of ball into unbeaten egg white and press onto nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and frost generously.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside. Blend butter, sugars, water and vanilla. Beat eggs.
Add flour mixture. Mix well; stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 50 cookies.

title: mom's corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: angel food pie-cake
directions: Crumble up cake in 9 x 13-inch pan or two casserole dishes. Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk with mixer until smooth. Spread over cake. Pour your favorite pie filling over the cream cheese layer. Mix large Cool Whip with 1/4 or 1/2 cup coconut. Spread over pie filling. Top with chopped pecans. Chill overnight.

title: eula's pate
directions: Turn into plastic wrap lined bowl.
Refrigerate.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: joyce's caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda; this will cause mixture to fizz.
Spray large metal dishpan or mixing bowl with Pam spray.
Pour syrup mixture over 7 quarts popped corn and blanched peanuts.
Mix well together and place in 250° oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in same dish you will be baking in.
Mix flour, sugar, and milk together.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour in dish with butter.
DO NOT STIR.
Spoon in peaches.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until light brown.

title: vidalia casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam or grease with margarine. Cover bottom of pan with sliced zucchini. Cover zucchini with sliced fresh tomatoes. Cover with crushed saltine crackers. Pour melted margarine over crackers. Sprinkle with about 1/2 cup shredded cheese. Sprinkle with about 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: With mixer, beat eggs for 1 minute; add flour, milk and salt. Beat
for
minutes; melt 6 tablespoons butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour
in
batter;
bake
at
for 10 to 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and continue to bake for
15 minutes.
(It
will
grow
bubbly
and
curl as it is baking.)

title: aruba cucumber lamb
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
In a large kettle, brown meat in oil.
Remove meat
and set aside.
Drain kettle, reserving 3 tablespoons oil.

Add to kettle the onions, celery, green pepper and fresh chilies (if you use them). Saute until limp. Return meat to kettle along with dried, crushed red pepper (if you use it), garlic, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add water, if necessary.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You need 1 brown grocery bag.

title: kolackies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Roll out thin on a board or countertop dusted with confectioners sugar. Cut out rounds with biscuit or donut cutter. Place a teaspoon of filling (fruit or nut filling) in the center of round. Bring 2 sides together and pinch to seal.

title: miniature biscuits
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with flour and sour cream.
Bake in miniature muffin tins at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: southern sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into small balls by hand. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Yields 48 balls.

title: rob's cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Grease spring-form pan and coat with graham cracker mixture.
Beat room temperature cream cheese, eggs, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Pour into prepared spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on top of cooled cake.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Wait 8 hours or overnight to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bones and cut into small pieces. Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine and put over chicken.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti and vegetables(serves 6)
directions: Cooked spaghetti and drain, toss with 1 tablespoon butter. Saute pepper onion, celery and mushrooms in butter; defrost broccoli in microwave and drain.
Add broccoli to sauteed vegetables.
Cook until tender, layer spaghetti in buttered shallow casserole dish, then cheese, then vegetable.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese on top of vegetable.
Mix milk with soup.
Add a pinch of cayenne.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle generously with paprika. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; shape
into loaf in shallow baking pan. Arrange with slices of
bacon.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let
stand
for
minutes
before
slicing; makes 4 servings.
Recipe can be doubled for 8 servings.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Raisins and nuts may be added.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough with a rolling pin until it looks almost like a pizza dough, about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle dough with pepper or garlic powder (your preference). Cover dough with cheese and pepperoni.
Roll dough into a loaf. Take the edge of the bread and roll up (almost like a jelly roll). Pinch the edges so that it doesn't unfold.
Place loaf on a cookie sheet.
Cook 30 minutes or until brown.
Brush beaten egg on top of loaf to make it look glazed.

title: nut and lentil roast
directions: Put nuts and onion through food grinder or processor.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, mushroom soup, sour cream, water chestnuts, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with fried onions.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: cowboy breakfast
directions: Preheat 14-inch Dutch oven.
Cut ham into 1-inch cubes. Place ham in
Dutch oven and fry for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove the ham, leaving
the drippings in the oven.
Scrub the potatoes and slice them leaving the skins on.	Place potato slices in heated Dutch oven.
Brown
and cover potatoes for 20 to 30 minutes.
Return ham
to
Dutch
oven
and mix with potatoes. Scramble the eggs
in a bowl with milk, salt and pepper.
Add egg mixture
to
ham
and potatoes.	Stir
until the eggs are cooked.
Cover
for
10 minutes.
Bacon can be substituted for ham.
Chopped
onions, cheese,
diced green chili and oregano can be added for variety.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Trim off coarse ends of asparagus.
Cut asparagus into 1-inch pieces.
Combine asparagus and 1 cup broth in medium saucepan. Cook 12 to 15 minutes until tender.

title: sticky buns
directions: Put the frozen yeast bread rolls into buttered Bundt pan.
Pour the pudding (dry) over the rolls.
Sprinkle the nuts over the bread.
Bring the butter, cinnamon and brown sugar to a boil and pour over bread.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter; stir in rice and cook on high heat until rice is browned.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on high for 4 to 6 minutes, then on medium-low heat for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding following package directions.
Mix in condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and filling in a glass bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, onion, tomatoes, cheese, hamburger and beans.

title: easy vegetable quiche
directions: Prick pie crust well with fork. Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 8 minutes. Remove to wire rack. Cool crust slightly. Lower oven temperature to 325°. Saut onion, green pepper and garlic in margarine in large skillet until soft. Remove from heat; cool slightly. Beat eggs in a large bowl until frothy. Stir in sauteed vegetables, cheese, salt, pepper, marjoram and the cooked vegetables. Pour mixture into crust. Bake in a moderate oven (325°) for 40 minutes, until center is firm. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: cajun shrimp and potato patties
directions: Boil shrimp and chill.
After chilled, grind up shrimp.
Boil potatoes and mash.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make patties out of mixture.
Fry in a skillet with 1 inch of oil until golden brown.

title: cream cheese vegetable dip
directions: Whip softened cream cheese.
Blend in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add seasonings.
Chill.

title: hot fudge sundae dessert(make at least 4 to 5 days before you want to serve)
directions: Grease lightly one 9 x 13-inch cake pan with margarine.
Mix margarine and Oreo cookies; spread in bottom of pan and cover with foil.
Freeze for 1 day.
Then spread softened ice cream over frozen cookie mixture, cover and freeze again for 1 day.

Combine sugar, 1 stick margarine, chocolate chips and evaporated milk in saucepan and bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly. When this mixture is completely cooled, pour over ice cream and freeze again for 1 day.
Spread Cool Whip over all of mixture and top with crushed peanuts.
Keep in freezer, covered until ready to serve.
Re-freeze any remaining dessert.

title: helen's fruit fizz punch
directions: In a large
pitcher,
pour
water over tea bags, brew 4 minutes, remove tea bags.
In a punch bowl, combine tea juices and lemonade.
Before
serving, add ginger ale and ice.
Makes 20 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix listed ingredients and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Use liquids from fruit to mix with pudding mix.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine meat and onion and brown on top of stove.
Combine with remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix
hamburger,
bread	crumbs,
milk, salt and pepper. Roll into small balls and put in large casserole dish.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells and bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain excess fat.
Cook elbow noodles according to package directions.
Combine ground chuck, elbow noodles and sauces in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put shredded Mozzarella cheese on top and then the pepperoni slices.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Recipe will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: homemade slippery pot pie
directions: Put beef chunks in large pot.
Cover with water; add bouillon cubes, onion slices and parsley.
Cook until tender.
Add potatoes.
Cook them for about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, make up dough mixture with flour, a pinch of salt and 2 1/2 cups broth. Mix to form a ball.
Roll out dough.
Cut in squares.
Add to broth in pot.
Cook until dough is tender.
Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add onions and saute for a few minutes.
Add cheese and eggs; heat until cheese melts. Add broccoli and stir until coated.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crackers.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat the eggs for five minutes.
Add sugar.
Stir in lemon and pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured cake roll pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in souffle dish at 350° about 1 hour.
Don't overbake.

title: tuna dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; set aside. Heat to boiling the tomato soup. Add cream cheese, then add gelatin. Chill until slightly firm. Add remaining ingredients. Chill in a mold oiled with Wesson oil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, sift flour with soda and salt.
Add sugars, egg, vanilla and butter.
With wooden spoon or portable electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth and well combined, about 1 minute.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces. Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Remove from oven; cool.

title: mrs. mac's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour with salt; alternate with milk. Add extract; stir in coconut.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes in a tube pan.

title: luau appetizers
directions: Cut 10 water chestnuts in half and quarter five chicken livers.
Wrap a piece of each in a half slice of bacon.
Fasten with wooden pick.
Chill in mixture of soy sauce and brown sugar about four hours.
Spoon marinade over occasionally.
Drain. Broil 3 inches from heat until bacon is crisp, turning once. Makes 20 appetizers.

title: superman pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook, flip and top with butter, syrup or fresh fruit.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend sugar, butter and extract.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Decorate with raisins to make faces if desired.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into muffin pans.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine water and sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine bananas and 3 cups pineapple juice in blender and blend until smooth.
Stir banana mixture into cooled syrup.
Stir in remaining pineapple juice, thawed lemonade, orange juice and lemon juice.
Pour into plastic containers and freeze for several hours before serving.
To serve, let stand at room temperature 15 to 30 minutes and mix with white soda.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased wide mouth pint jars, filling them 1/2 full of batter.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine water, sugar and coffee.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add vanilla and vodka.
Store in brown bottle.

title: tuna three or four bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve cold.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce. Season with oregano, garlic and salt to taste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender.
Layer in buttered casserole dish:
sauce, noodles, sauce, cheese.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Lay crackers in one layer on a cookie sheet with sides.
Cut each cracker in half as they are marked.
Melt in heavy saucepan the butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour over graham crackers and spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While slightly warm, cut apart. Remove from cookie sheet when cold.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and potato soup.
Add shrimp, horseradish, onion and salt and pepper.
Layer half in a dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Cover with half of the cheese.
Layer once again and top with 1/3 cup sliced almonds.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with crackers.

title: scallop cream sauce
directions: Blend scallops, onion, salt, pepper and water in a saucepan . Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Save 1 cup of liquid.
Melt butter; blend in flour, paprika and oregano; add liquid and milk. Cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir a small amount of mixture into egg; add egg to mixture.
Add scallops.

title: chicken-melon salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, grapes and celery.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, chutney, curry powder and salt until smooth. Pour over chicken mixture.
Toss until well blended.
Place cantaloupe wedges on pieces of lettuce.
Spoon chicken salad on top of wedges.

title: easy tuna salad
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, mix first 3 ingredients.
Add 1 1/2 cups potato chips; mix thoroughly.
Pour other 1/2 cup chips on top.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven about 45 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: pork and bean bake
directions: Fry 4 strips of bacon until crisp and crumble.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Combine ingredients and season to taste.
Place in baking dish and place 3 strips of bacon over this.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly and bacon is done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding and set aside.
Cut up bananas and put cookies up the sides and the bananas.
Slowly pour 1/3 of the pudding in the dish and stop, put a layer of cookies and a layer of bananas.
Put another 1/3 of the pudding, stop, a layer of cookies and a layer of bananas.
Then put the last of the pudding and top it with a layer of bananas and a layer of cookies.

title: white hot chocolate
directions: Heat cream and milk but don't boil. Turn off heat and add white chocolate and vanilla. Serve immediately.

title: pepper steak
directions: Blend soy sauce, water, cornstarch, pepper and garlic.
Slice steak across grain and mix into soy sauce mixture.
Heat oil and add peppers till tender.
Mix in drained meat and cook till brown. Stir in tomatoes and soy sauce mixture and simmer until tender. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: st. peter's sin dessert
directions: Pastry:
Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter; mix well.
Add chilies, garlic salt and corn.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, diced onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Mix with soup and vegetables.
Pour in casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top and bake at 350° until biscuits are done.
Serves 4.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add Crisco.
Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Mix and pour onto floured board.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise about 1 hour in a warm place.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Brush top with margarine when done.

title: sole in almond butter
directions: In a 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) glass baking dish, combine almonds and butter.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes or until butter and almonds are golden brown.
Stir in lemon juice, wine, dill and salt.
Arrange fillets in butter mixture, spooning sauce over fillets.
Cook, covered with wax paper or plastic wrap, 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes before serving.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices or dill pickle slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown sausage; place in casserole dish.
Saute onions, combine rice and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over sausage, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: borch
directions: Divide 3/4 pound butter into 3 pieces.
Put 1 piece butter and tomatoes in pan.
Heat and then simmer.
Fry in frying pan 1 piece butter, minced onions, 2 quarts shredded cabbage and 1 carrot (finely shredded).
Fry to golden brown.
Put water in 6-quart pot and boil.
Add 6 cups cubed potatoes, beet and salt.
When potatoes are done, remove and add tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Mash potatoes with last piece butter and 1/2 of cream.
Add potatoes and remainder of cream to pot.
Boil 1 minute.
Add onions, cabbage, remaining raw cabbage and potatoes.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Remove beet and discard.
Serve.
Garnish with green pepper or dill leaves, minced.

title: cheese buttons
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bring cheese and margarine to room temperature and mix by hand.
Add salt, pepper and Rice Krispies. Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and mash with fork. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chess pie *
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage ball appetizers
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: make ahead lemonade base for lemon drinks
directions: Combine sugar and water in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool 20 minutes.
Add lemon peel and lemon juice to sugar syrup.
Pour into covered jar and chill.
Store base in refrigerator for up to 3 days.
Makes 5 cups of base.
Use to make lemonade, Lemon Sherbet Float, Strawberry-Lemonade Slush and Tropical Lemon Iced Tea.

title: crunch bars
directions: crush 4 cups cereal and spread evenly into a 13 X 9 pan.
Top with peanuts, raisins, chocolate chips, and remaining 2 cups of uncrushed cereal.
Drizzle milk over the mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars. Store tightly covered.

title: anginetti cream puffs
directions: Prepare Anginetti by slicing off tops.
Hold tops aside. Drain crushed pineapple, leaving a little juice.
Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together in a bowl for about 1 minute at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple and blend all 3 ingredients for about 1 minute at low speed.
Drop filling from tablespoon onto bottom layer of cookies, replacing tops.
Refrigerate puffs until ready to serve.
May be frozen on a cookie sheet.
After freezing, remove from sheet and store in a freezer box with waxed paper between layers.
May be eaten 10 to 15 minutes after removing from freezer.
Filling should be enough to fill all or most of the cookies in the package (about 23).
You can dot top of puffs with any leftover filling for extra decoration.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease cookie sheets.
Cream butter, then gradually add the 2 sugars, beating until light and smooth. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda together and then add to mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts or oatmeal (optional).
Drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Cream butter with cheese, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in strawberries.
Spoon into jar.
Cover and refrigerate.
(Good with hot biscuits or toast.)

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil raisins, water, sugar and shortening for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add soda and hot water and mix.
Add salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon; mix all together.
Add enough flour to the above batter to make the consistency of cake batter.
Add nuts.
Grease 2 regular loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Combine water with spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Brown 2 pounds hamburger.
Drain fat off.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with a little water.
Put in layers lasagne noodles (do not cook), hamburger, cheeses and sauce.
Add another layer until all is used up.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are done.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Can be made the day before.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown
hamburger
and onions.
Drain.
Stir
in
tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Cook over low
heat
for
5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon
about 1/4 cup meat mixture into biscuit-lined cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until
golden brown.
Yields 12 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour and salt in medium saucepan. Gradually stir in milk and yolks. Cook, stirring constantly 8 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and Equal in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom crust.
Pour 1 cup milk and pudding mix into bowl and mix with wire whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes). Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spice with wire whisk. Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Garnish with whipped topping and nuts (optional).

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, green pepper and onion.
Marinate overnight or longer in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Makes a large salad.

title: mud pie chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Make three holes in mixture and pour oil into the first hole, vinegar in the second hole and vanilla in the third hole.
Beat eggs with water in a small bowl and pour over dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Stir with a fork until evenly blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched with fingertips. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, milk and extracts. Beat well.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans or 5 to 6 mini loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix the Pace Thick & Chunky with the olives and green chilies.
Take 1 tortilla and spread it with cream cheese, then spoon on some of the Pace mixture, covering about 1/2 the surface of the tortilla.
Carefully roll up the tortilla and wrap it in plastic wrap.
Continue with each tortilla until you run out of the Pace mixture.
Refrigerate the wrapped tortillas at least 6 hours, then cut each into 1/2 inch pieces to serve.
These are very easy to make and good to eat!

title: sweet sliced pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/8-inch thick, after washing thoroughly. Slice peeled onions likewise.
Cut pepper into fine bits.
Mix salt through combined cucumbers, onions and pepper in crock or large plastic container.
Place weighted lid on mixture.
Let stand 3 hours, pouring off liquid about every hour and then stirring.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook onions and garlic in drippings.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: katherine's peach fuzz
directions: Mix all in blender and serve.

title: raspberry custard
directions: Beat the eggs slightly with an eggbeater.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Add the raspberries last.
Put the custard in a casserole and set it in a pie plate filled with water.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° to finish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until set.
The center may still look a bit soft, but this will set later.
Cooking too long makes the custard watery.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in 1/2-inch slices.
Brown meat in hot oil in large skillet or Dutch oven. Add garlic, tomatoes and 1 cup water to browned meat.
Lower and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Add green peppers, onions and celery.
Cover and cook until pepper strips are tender.
Combine cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and stir until smooth. Stir into meat and vegetable mixture. Add Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: prune sour cream coffee cake
directions: Pour boiling water
over
prunes, let stand 15 minutes. Drain pit and
dice
prunes,
add
lemon	rind
and set aside. Grease and flour
9-inch tube pan, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda
and
salt,
remove
1/4 cup and toss with prunes. Cream butter
and
sugar
until fluffy, beat in eggs, one at a time,
slowly beat in flour mixture.
Alternate with sour cream and
vanilla, beginning and ending with flour, fold in prunes. Combine
brown
sugar, cinnamon and nuts, turn 1/3 batter
into pan.
Sprinkle
with
brown
sugar
mixture, repeat layering twice.
Bake
at
350° for 55 minutes or until done, cool in pan on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken soup mexican(from sheryl's sister, ginger roman)
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth and cut up.
(I add celery, carrots and onions to cook chicken in for a more flavorful broth.) Cook onions in melted margarine until transparent.
Sprinkle flour over onions, stirring constantly.
Add half and half and chicken broth.
Continue stirring over medium heat until thick. Add corn, cheese, chilies, chicken and spices.
Stir well.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, and salt.
Set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter, water, shortening and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Stir well.
In another bowl, dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and add to rest of mixture.
Bake in 15 x 10 pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: mounds chocolate cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake mix
as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool
and
slice crosswise thru cake.
Make filling of
sugar,
milk, marshmallows and coconut; cook until thick.
Spread on 1/2 cake.
Top filling with other 1/2 cake.

title: stuffed-tomato clowns
directions: Peel the tomatoes, if desired.
With sharp knife at slant, cut out from each tomato a cone from end opposite stem; reserve.
Scoop out half of center.
Invert tomatoes and chill.
Combine eggs, celery, olives and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Chill. Just before serving, add mayonnaise; mix well.
Sprinkle inside of tomatoes with salt; heap with salad.
Perch cone; point.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: Take the power of the Holy Spirit as your spoon and mix together love and loyalty.
Add faith and mix thoroughly.
Blend in tenderness, kindness and understanding.
Add friendship and hope.
Sprinkle abundantly with laughter.
Bake it with sunshine and serve daily!

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: In a medium bowl, mix stuffing, melted butter and 1 1/4 cups chicken broth.
Mix chicken, 3/4 cup broth, onion, chives, celery, mayonnaise and salt in another bowl.
Spread 1/2 the stuffing in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Spread chicken mixture over stuffing.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Whisk eggs, milk and soup together.
Pour sauce evenly over stuffing.
Cover with foil. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake for additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together well 4 eggs, 2/3 cup water, 1 cup salad oil and a can of pumpkin; mix.
Then sift and add 3 1/3 cups flour, 2 teaspoons soda, 1 1/2 teaspoon salt, 3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and pinch of cloves.
Pour into 2 bread pans lightly greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes ala elegant
directions: Mash potatoes without milk.
Add cream cheese, 1 egg, onion and salt.
Blend well.
Fold in pimento.
Dot with butter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl; stir.

title: ham-cheese oven omelet
directions: Beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish or square 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, in oven until omelet is set and top is golden brown, 40 to 45 minutes, at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: quick and easy pork roll meal
directions: Split English muffins in half and place on cookie sheet. Next, slice pork roll and place one slice on each muffin half. Place pineapple ring next and then top with mashed sweet potato. Place in oven and bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon sour cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and oil and add sour cream last on medium speed until creamy.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured funnel pan.
Mix the 3 teaspoons sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon together.
Sprinkle half of this over 1/2 cake batter. Swirl with knife.
Pour rest of batter and sprinkle the other cinnamon and sugar over batter.
Swirl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fish soup creole gumbo
directions: Simmer onion and ham together until onion is cooked.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer about 1 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread over beef.
Add 3 cups water.
Cover.
Bake 4 hours at 325°.
Refrigerate the broth overnight; take any grease off and strain the grease and pour over the thinly sliced beef.
Serve on Italian rolls or any hard rolls.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Press beef into 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with onions to taste.
Pour over this the soup, the corn and top with Tater Tots. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients, cutting in the shortening as you would do for a pie crust.
Stir in the buttermilk and water/yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly; the dough is now ready to be refrigerated or made into biscuits.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: chile and cheese squares
directions: Grate cheese and layer with chilies in greased casserole dish. Beat 3 eggs with 1 tablespoon milk and one tablespoon of flour. Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool well before cutting.
An 8 or 9-inch dish works best.

title: mini cherry cheesecakes
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until creamy.
Put vanilla wafers in cupcake liners of muffin tin.
Add cream cheese mixture (heaping tablespoonful) about 3/4 way full.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes (until top cracks).
Top with cherries.
Makes 24.

title: yummy green beans
directions: String the beans; wash well and boil rapidly in salted water uncovered until barely tender and firm (taste them to make sure). Drain and run under cold water to stop the cooking.
Pat dry. Melt butter and add garlic; cook gently until softened.
Do not brown.
Pour over beans and taste for seasoning.
May be made ahead.
To reheat, put in microwave for 2 minutes on High or heat in saucepan over low heat.

title: lasagne
directions: Prepare meat sauce:
Over high heat, cook beef and onions until done; drain fat.
Add tomatoes with liquid and next 8 ingredients. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes stirring often. Prepare lasagne noodles as per directions; drain.
In bowl, mix Ricotta and eggs.

title: lillian's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Blend sour cream.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased tube pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 on top of batter.
Pour on other 1/2 of batter and top with rest of cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: summertime banana pie
directions: Combine crumbs, walnuts and butter in bowl and mix well. Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Combine milk and pudding mix in bowl.
Beat for five minutes.
Fold in sour cream.
Arrange bananas in prepared pan.
Spoon pudding over bananas.
Chill for several hours.

title: sour cream pastries
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Combine egg yolk and sour cream, then blend into flour mixture. Form dough into ball; refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Divide dough into 4 pieces; take out 1 piece at a time from refrigerator and roll into 10-inch circle.
Spread 2 tablespoons of apricot preserves over circle; cut into 12 wedges with a pastry wheel.
Roll wedges from outside edge towards center.
Sprinkle each pastry with sugar; bake at 350° for 20 minutes in an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: syrian green beans
directions: Brown meat halfway in butter.
Add onions and brown with meat. Add salt, pepper and cut green beans.
Add crushed tomatoes and cook slowly, 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Very good served over hot buttered rice.

title: arizona carrot casserole
directions: Peel and slice carrots in circles.
Boil in consomme until tender; drain.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cover with soup and almonds.
Season with salt, pepper and dry mustard; mix well. Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian fruit bars
directions: In a bowl combine ingredients in order given.
Mix after each addition with wire whip or electric mixer.
Pour batter into 8 x 8 inch nonstick pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Loosen cake from pan with a spatula.
Cut into bars, dividing equally into 4 portions.
Serves 4.

title: lemon herb tea
directions: Add boiling water to ingredients.
Steep 5 to 10 minutes.

title: simple tomato cabbage
directions: Cover chopped cabbage with water and bring to a boil.
Spill off water and add tomato juice and barley.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until barley is soft, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, cornmeal, oil, salt and garlic salt.
Add eggs, milk and peppers.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until solid in middle.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Put 1 cup water and 1 stick margarine into a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup flour.
Add 4 beaten eggs.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Let cool 1/2 hour.

title: chicken soup(low calorie)
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until done.
Makes 8 servings.
One serving equals 77 calories or 1 lean meat and 1 vegetable exchange.

title: beef bacon chowder
directions: Fry bacon till crisp and drain.
Cook celery and onion with meat.
When meat is done, drain and add all ingredients and heat on low so it won't burn on.

title: baked rice(old family recipe)
directions: In a deep baking dish, brown the beef; drain fat.
Add garlic, tomato paste, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Heat on top of stove for a few minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add raw rice. Mix well.
Add eggs and cheese; mix again.
Add hot water and stir.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix vegetables, chicken, and soup in a ungreased 9 in. pie plate. Stir remaining ingredients until blended. Pour into pie plate and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. 6 servings.

title: 9-day cole slaw
directions: Let stand cabbage, peppers, onions and sugar, then prepare Wesson oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and celery.
Bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage.
Stir well to dissolve sugar.
Cool well before serving.
Flavor improves with age.

title: rosemary-peppercorn vinegar
directions: Put into a bottle the rosemary sprigs and, if desired, fresh lemon thyme sprigs.
Add whole black peppercorns and fill with white vinegar.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition. Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa together; add 1/2 at a time with buttermilk to the creamed mixture, then add vanilla and food coloring. Stir well and pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and put in bread pan.
Bake slowly.
Baste with brown sugar, water and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Sometimes too much water is added to meat.
I usually have to draw juice off before I baste.
Takes about 2 hours at 350°. Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend ingredients together and bake in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with crumbled bread.
Cook sausage in skillet until done.
Drain off fat; blot sausage between paper towels.
Mix sausage with mustard; sprinkle sausage evenly over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage. (If casserole will not be cooked the same day, stop here and freeze the sausage and bread mixture.)
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until set in middle.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until soft but firm.
Cut bacon into small pieces; fry until well done.
Drain and dispose of fat.
Chop pickles and set aside.
Chop medium onions into small pieces. Boil, peel and chop hard-boiled eggs.
Mix all ingredients together plus salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with Hellmann's real mayonnaise to taste.
Serve warm.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, and powdered sugar.
Put in bottom of pie crusts.
Mix lemon pudding mix as directed on the box.
Pour over top of cheese mixture.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: In small saucepan bring 2 cups water to boil.
Stir in rice. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, using a 10-inch skillet, cook eggs in margarine.
Add chopped onion and the rice until mixture is lightly browned.
Mix 2/3 cup water with 5 or 6 tablespoons soy sauce and stir into rice.
Heat until water is absorbed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend all together and roll into several small balls or size needed.
Roll ingredients in pecans.
Makes 2 large cheese balls. This may be frozen until needed.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch Pyrex dish or individual paper muffin cups.
Freeze.
Defrost large dish 1 hour.
Cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook beef and onion; drain.
Stir in taco mix.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: fix ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan.
Add water to cover and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain and peel potatoes.
Place in large mixing bowl and mash with a potato masher.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine and next 4 ingredients, mixing until all ingredients are blended.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or Cool Whip.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in pineapple.
Pour on hot cake.

title: long sermon chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or spray with Pam.
Spread rice in pan; lay chicken on top.
Combine soups and water; pour over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 375°, 1 1/2 hours at 350°, 3 hours at 275° to 300° or forever at 225°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light. Add to creamed mixture.
Add mashed bananas and buttermilk, mixing well.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and put in pie shell.
Freeze.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter and place in pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Smooth on top of graham crackers.
Top with one can of Thank You pie filling cherries or a filling of your choice.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Mix chicken, salsa, sour cream, chili powder and salt together.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread refried beans evenly over tortillas.
Spoon chicken mixture across center of tortilla. Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up and place seam side down in baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serve with lettuce and tomatoes on top.

title: breakfast pork sausage patties
directions: Mix well together with hands.
Make into patties.
Either use immediately or place in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and pepper.
Saute until onion is translucent, but not brown.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Shape into desired form.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 9 to 11.

title: mom's yummy cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries, oranges and apples in food processor.
Add sugar to taste.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: cooper's chili con carne
directions: Heat olive oil in a 6-quart saucepan.
Add meat to oil and sear over high heat, stirring constantly, until meat is gray, not brown.
The seared meat should have the consistency of whole grain hominy.
Add water; cover and cook at a bubbly simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add all other ingredients, except flour and cornmeal. Cook for 30 minutes (further cooking will cause the spices to loose their flavor).
Mix flour and cornmeal with enough water to form a paste; add to chili.
Bring mixture back to boil.
(You can add more chili powder to suit your taste.)

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Use a rolling pin to flatten each piece of bread.
Combine Blue cheese, cream cheese and egg in bowl and mix well.
Spread evenly on bread, covering each slice to the edges.
Place 1 asparagus spear (or 2 to 3 cut pieces) on each slice of bread and roll up and secure with 3 toothpicks.
Dip in melted butter.
Place on a baking sheet and freeze.
Partially thaw asparagus rolls and slice each into 3 equal pieces so each piece has a toothpick.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Yields 60 appetizers.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown ground beef in margarine.
Add other ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix well and cook in lightly greased (10-inch) pan for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter and add wet ingredients. Mix well until dough is smooth.
Does not need a lot of kneading. Put in large Tupperware bowl and seal.
Keep in warm place for 1 hour, or until bubbly and at least double in size.
Form into a loaf and place in oiled pan.
Let rise another 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until nicely browned.
Store in cloth kitchen towel until used up or freeze as soon as covered. Do not refrigerate!

title: maple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
In medium bowl, stir egg, melted butter, 1/2 cup maple syrup and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until just blended.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour batter in muffin tins.
In small bowl, stir together the brown sugar, pecans and remaining maple syrup.
Spoon over muffins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Remove pans to wire rack; let cool 5 minutes.
A great way to start a cool Fall morning.

title: party seafood dip
directions: Put cream cheese on a serving dish.
Pile shrimp or crab on top.
Pour on seafood sauce.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add sour cream. Using a Bundt pan (greased), put 1/2 batter and 1/2 of apple mix, then rest of batter and apple mix on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let set 1/2 hour before removing from pan.
When cooled, put on any frosting glaze.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: pumpkin pie coffee creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an air-tight container. Add to your morning's coffee and enjoy!

title: baked squash
directions: Cut up, boil and mash squash.
Add remaining ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Butter baking dish and bake at 375° until done.
Tastes a lot like dressing.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Place the sweet potatoes in a baking dish.
In medium saucepan, combine sugars, cornstarch, orange rind and salt. Slowly stir in juice and water.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, cook until thickened.
Stir in butter until melted. Pour over sweet potatoes; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: tart balls
directions: Mix and shape into round balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar or coconut.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat over night in crock pot, covered with water. Drain in the morning and return meat to crock pot. Add the rest of the ingredients and cook on high all day. Serve with Fritos, shredded cheese, green onions, sour cream and your favorite hot sauce.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring mixture of sugar, syrup, butter and salt to a boil; cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 teaspoon soda and cream of tartar.
Pour over popped corn; mix well.
Put in pan; bake in oven for 1 hour at 200°.
Remove from oven; place on waxed paper and separate.
After it is cool, place in sealed jar or plastic bag.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Tear head of lettuce in bite size pieces and put in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Cover top with mayonnaise to seal.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Next day toss and add croutons and serve.
Serves 8.

title: baked chicken and stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package. Cook chicken until done.
Remove chicken from bones.
Place chicken in a 3 x 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all 3 soups together. Do not dilute.
