Pour over chicken. Place stuffing over chicken and soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil soup, water and chicken.
Add peas and rice.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scott casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix sour cream with cooked noodles. Add chopped onion.
Combine tomatoes and tomato sauce.
In a sprayed casserole dish, layer beef, noodles, tomato mixture, grated cheese and more layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: reindeer sandwiches
directions: Spread peanut butter on bread.	Use raisins for eyes, a cherry for the nose and pretzels for the antlers.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Mix all together and simmer for about 2 hours. Put in jars and seal.

title: nutty apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill 18 greased muffin cups three fourths full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: t-cakes
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Chill dough and roll.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: faye's scalloped pineapple
directions: Put pineapple and crumbs into baking dish.
Mix beaten eggs, sugar and butter together.
Pour over pineapple and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy teacake bread
directions: Whip together sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in flour until moist.
Pour into 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook at 350° until top is lightly browned and puffiness has fallen down.

title: 7 seven slaw
directions: Chop all veggies together; drain well.
Set aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil; pour over cabbage mixture while hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Beat together egg, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let cool completely.
Remove from pan.
Makes a 3 pound loaf.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese, lettuce and croutons.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Break up Romano in small pieces.
Add cheese and croutons.
Toss with dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: super bowl beans
directions: Fry bacon until nearly done; drain well on paper towel.
Fry hamburger and onion; drain off excess grease.
In a large Dutch oven or baking dish, combine remaining ingredients.
Add meats and onion; simmer for 4 to 5 hours on the stove, or bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, then add dry ingredients. Roll into 1-inch diameter balls and place in small muffin pan.
Bake until light brown at 350° about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and press a peanut butter cup in the middle. Cool slightly before removing.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan and bring to boil, then reduce heat to simmering.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add broccoli, onion and bay leaves.
Reduce heat and simmer until broccoli is tender; remove bay leaves.
Meanwhile, in another saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is hot and thickened stirring often.
Add 1 cup of broccoli to milk mixture; stir until blended.
Gradually add remaining broccoli stock to milk mixture. Heat and stir until well-blended.
Season with salt and pepper. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes but do not peel.
Cut into quarters; cook, then drain.
Place half of the potatoes in a baking dish and season to taste.
Add half of the cheese and bacon.
Repeat the layer and pour butter over the top.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cook
roast.
Mix
the rest of ingredients.
Put it all together and
add
the beef broth and some of the beef, cut in small pieces.
Add	salt
and pepper to taste.
Cook until the flavor has cooked through.	Then enjoy.

title: slush
directions: Heat, dissolve and chill sugar and water. Add the next 4 ingredients.
Pour into containers and freeze. Serve with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: chewies
directions: Mix in order given and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven in a greased pan.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until soft.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: beef and tators
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart dish.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes in microwave.
Stir and turn 2 times.
Add onion and Tater Tots. Mix soups and pour over mixture.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Turn 3 times.

title: potato pie
directions: Put cottage cheese through food mill to make it smooth.
Beat potatoes in with cheese. Beat in sour cream, eggs, salt and cayenne pepper. Stir in scallions; spoon into uncooked pie shell and sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight to
blend and flavor.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.
Also good on fish or baked potatoes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Process all ingredients and mold into a ball or shape of your choice.
Serve with strawberry preserves on gingersnaps.
(I pour the preserves over the mold and serve gingersnaps on the side.)

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Beat together the eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Add the cooked spaghetti and mix to coat.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer the spaghetti mixture and the Mozzarella cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cover to bake.
Cut into squares and serve with your favorite spaghetti sauce.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Take a large soup pot.
Put 1 tablespoon of oil and 1 cut onion in; brown this a little with the meat.
Fill soup pot with water, about 3/4 of the pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add to water all spices and bay leaves.
Cook on medium heat for about 30 minutes.
Add tomato soup, tomatoes, sugar, lemon juice and kosher salt.
Cut cabbage; take core out and place in boiling soup.
Cook for 2 hours approximately, continuing stirring.
Peel potatoes; cut into small pieces.
Put into soup.
Cook for approximately 1 more hour.
Add toasted almonds.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Mix and pour over any fruit.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve warm or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: christmas snowballs
directions: Soften cream cheese, add vanilla.
Mix into plain sugar, 1/2 at a time.
Stir in 2 cups coconut, mix and then roll into balls of coconut.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, waters, pineapple and pie filling.
Chill in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and pecans.
Pour over Jell-O mixture.
Chill.

title: pot roast
directions: Wipe pot roast with damp paper towel.
Brown well in butter in 6-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, turning with wooden spoons. Remove roast and set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Add onion and garlic to drippings and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add vinegar, corn syrup and broth.
Stir while bringing to a boil.
Tie bay leaves, parsley and pepper in cheesecloth.
Add to pot with roast.
Cover and put into oven and bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove cheesecloth bag before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Remove outer leaves from cabbage.
Shred cabbage; cover with boiling water.
Boil for 5 minutes; drain.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper; beat until smooth.
Stir in cabbage and pour into casserole dish.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy orange salad
directions: Place in bowl:
Jell-O, pudding and tapioca.
Mix well. Slowly pour water over, stirring to dissolve.
Let cool and partially congeal, then add Cool Whip and mix well.
Blend in oranges.
Mold; refrigerate.

title: frozen fruit delight
directions: Beat cream cheese in small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Combine the two mixtures and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan; freeze.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chefs salad
directions: Chop onions, tomatoes, lettuce. Toss with cheese, dressing and hot sauce. Add Doritos. Add sliced avocado. Brown beef, drain, add beans, and salt. Simmer for 10 minutes. Mix into cold salad. Decorate with Doritos, avocado and sliced tomatoes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 13 ingredients.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish (dish will be full).
Sprinkle with cheese and French-fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg yolks and 2 tablespoons of milk and bring to a boil.
Simmer gently 20 minutes over low heat, stirring frequently. Beat together egg yolks with 2 tablespoons milk and add to hot rice, stirring rapidly.
Remove from heat and chill.
Place waxed paper directly on pudding to prevent crusting.

title: summer grilled steak
directions: Preheat the barbecue grill or the oven to broil.

title: fish ragout
directions: If fish is frozen, thaw enough to cut into 1-inch cubes or cut fresh fish into cubes.
Set aside.
In large, heavy pan such as a Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic in the oil until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, red and green pepper, cucumber, basil and oregano.
Saute 2 minutes more.
Add water and heat to simmering.
Add fish.
Heat to simmer and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish is just tender.
Cooking time depends on the type of fish and whether it is fresh or frozen.
Add salt and saffron. Just before serving, add lemon juice to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: asparagus and mushroom omelet
directions: Boil one inch of water in a large skillet. Add asparagus and cook, uncovered, just until crisp tender. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs and water until the whites and yolks are completely blended. Coat a 10 inch nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat the skillet over medium-high heat until just hot enough to sizzle when a drop of water is added. Pour in egg mixture. It should set immediately. With an inverted pancake turner, lift the edges as the mixture begins to set to allow the uncooked portion to flow underneath. When the top is set, fill one half of the omelet with the asparagus, mushrooms and cheese. With the pancake turner, fold the omelet in half over the filling. Slide onto serving plate. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve immediately. This has 5 grams of carbohydrate.

title: lemon angel roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut an 18-inch long piece of parchment paper.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter over parchment paper, spreading evenly using scraper.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.
Remove from oven to cooling rack.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of powdered sugar over cake.
Place a sheet of parchment paper over cake.
Place cooling rack upside down over parchment paper and carefully turn cake out at once.
Roll up cake in parchment paper as for a jelly roll.
Cool completely.
Unroll cake.
Spread cake with 1/4 cup ice cream topping, pressing lightly using a scraper. Combine cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Zest whole lemon.
Juice lemon to measure 1 tablespoon juice.
Add zest and juice to cream cheese mixture and whisk.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Mix well.
Fold in 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Gently spread ice cream topping to within 1-inch of edge. Reroll cake.
Sprinkle with remaining powdered sugar.
Slice with knife.
Garnish each serving with whipped topping, a strawberry and remaining ice cream topping.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pull apart
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Combine 1/4 cup white sugar and cinnamon. Shake biscuits thoroughly in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Thoroughly grease 10-inch fluted Bundt pan.
Arrange biscuits in prepared pan. In saucepan, combine margarine, sugars, milk and vanilla.
Bring to boiling point and pour over biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately onto warm platter.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch cake pans at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Top with strawberry icing by adding 1/2 cup crushed sweetened strawberries to a can of prepared cake frosting.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry 4 strips of bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Drain bacon drippings except for 2 tablespoons.
Add onions and green pepper. Saute until onions are clear.
Add 1 (16 ounce) can tomatoes and juice.
Add 1 cup of water and 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce.
Add seasonings (sugar, salt and pepper).
Add 2 cups of rice.
Pour into greased casserole and bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: irish italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in oil, add meat and seasonings, brown lightly. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add soups; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat condensed milk, pudding mix and water. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon into serving dishes. Chill. Garnish with whipped cream or as desired.

title: dirt cake
directions: Separate cookies; put the filling in one bowl and the cookies into the blender, a few at a time.
Blend until they look like potting soil.
Cream together butter, sugar, cream cheese and filling from the cookies.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix instant vanilla pudding and milk.
Beat until blended and fold in Cool Whip.

title: richard's fruit salad
directions: Mix together pie filling, oranges, strawberries and grapes. Chill well.
This can be done the day before serving.
Slice bananas into the fruit mixture just before serving.

title: swedish ham balls
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, egg and milk and mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake in slow oven (325°) 1 hour, basting frequently.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Set aside 15 1/2 X 10 1/2 X 1 inch pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. In separate bowl cream butter, peanut butter and vanilla until softened. Add eggs gradually, creaming until fluffy after each addition. Thoroughly blend in dry ingredients. Turn into pan and spread evenly. Bake at 375 degrees for about 20 minutes. Cut into 3 X 1 1/2 inch bars while warm. Remove.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Place fruit in layers in large bowl in order as
given.
Spoon orange juice concentrate on top.
Cover and chill for 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream blueberry pound cake
directions: Combine margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, three at a time.
Add 1/2 of sour cream and flour.
Blend.
Add remaining flour, soda, lemon and sour cream.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in blueberries.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip together and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: chicken rice broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix chicken, rice, broccoli in oven safe dish.
Melt the cheese, milk and soup.
Pour over ingredients, mix well and bake about 20 to 30 minutes, until thoroughly heated.
Serve.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: In large bowl, beat together raw eggs, ketchup, soup mix and spices.
Add bread crumbs; blend well.
Mix in ground beef.
Blend thoroughly with hands.
Pack 3/4 of mixture into standard size loaf pan.
Push 3 holes in center of loaf pan.
Place a peeled boiled egg in each hole, lengthwise.
Cover with remaining meat mixture, carefully packing down tightly and covering eggs.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cover with extra ketchup during the last 1/2 hour.
Cook 5 minutes.
Slices will have egg in almost every serving.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Put in bowl the first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with Doritos or nacho chips.
Serves 8 to 10.
Contains 204 calories.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Meanwhile, melt butter in glass container in microwave.
Blend in flour.
Add salt. Slowly blend in milk.
Add 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Microwave until thickened (about 4 minutes), stirring occasionally.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: peanut crunch bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a pan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Pack down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Fold in undrained pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tests done. Remove from pans to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pork chop and garden vegetables
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in butter in a large skillet. Drain.
Add carrot and next 3 ingredients.
Combine dry soup mix and water, mixing well.
Pour over chops and vegetables.
Bring to a boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Yields 2 servings.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix first layer and spread in bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: eileen's brownies
directions: Melt shortening.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, then shortening and blend.
Add flour, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour batter into waxed paper-lined 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 32.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar, pecans, corn syrup, vinegar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 325° and continue to bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Hard-boiled eggs may be added, if not kept too long.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Add macaroni, stirring enough to coat macaroni with margarine. Cover with 1 quart milk.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not stir. Check to see if macaroni is done.
If not, bake 5 or 10 minutes longer.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix soups together (no water).
Alternate layers of chicken breasts and soup in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 5 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
So easy and so delicious!

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together thoroughly. Add flour (part at a time) and form into rolls.
Chill overnight.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan or frypan.
Bring mixture to boil over medium heat.
Pour mixture over uncooked meat; cover.
Put in a 350° oven until meat is tender.

title: party jello mold
directions: Bring applesauce and water to boil.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into ring mold.
Chill.
Unmold and fill with cottage cheese or Waldorf salad.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: always good casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and butter.
Add meat and lightly brown until meat is no longer pink.
Add seasonings.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer like lasagne.
Place tomato sauce, meat mixture first, next uncooked noodles, then tomato sauce-meat and noodles (be sure noodles are well covered by sauce).
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 10.

title: oriental pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lima bean-tomato casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter; add onion and cook about 5 minutes. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and mix thoroughly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beans and ham; heat until bubbling.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread bread rounds with remaining butter (or melt butter and toss with crumbs).
Place rounds or crumbs in a border around casserole.
Broil about 10 minutes or until bread is delicately browned.
Or heat in 425° oven.
Serve 6.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3-quart pan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits together over hot, but not boiling, water (or microwave), stirring until well blended. Remove from heat and spread evenly over Krispies mixture.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: stir-fried chicken and broccoli
directions: In wok or heavy skillet, on medium-high heat, saute broccoli in vegetable oil.
After 5 minutes, add chicken strips.
Saute another 5 to 7 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull the strawberries.
Reserve half (the better looking ones) and mash the remainder.
To the mashed berries, add the sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well; cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.
Stir in lemon juice and almond flavoring.
Cool.
Add the remaining berries (whole ones). Pour into pie shell and chill.
Before serving, top with a ruff of whipped cream.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except flour; blend well.
Stir in flour.
Chill.
Preheat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured surface, roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes, until brown.
Frost.

title: italian beans
directions: Stir all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve hot!

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Add pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered wax paper.
Chill.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk.
Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg; stir in.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until browned. Can be topped with meringue, if desired.

title: cherry minute crisp
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.
Spoon cherry pie filling into 7x11 baking pan.
Sprinkle in the cake mix right from pkg.
Drizzle in butter.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve in ice cream.
Yield 6-8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of casserole dish. Top with 1 can of hot Hormel chili. Follow with green chilies, then second can of hot Hormel chili. Top with Cheddar cheese and black olives. Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar together until well blended and smooth, about 4 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, coconut, pecans and half of Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into crust and spread remaining Cool Whip over filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spinach and rice
directions: Saute onion and olive oil in large saucepan until transparent. Add rice and cook and brown slightly.
Add tomato sauce and washed spinach.
Stir occasionally.
As spinach cooks, so does the rice. Test rice and spinach to your desire.
Don't dry out, should have a slight liquidity to it.
Lemon juice is tasty on this.
Takes approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Bring butter, sugar, & milk to boil in sauce pot. Cook 8 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat. Add chocolate morsels & marshmallow cream. Mix well. Add pecans and vanilla. Pour into greased pan.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and meal.
Mix well.
Add melted margarine; mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and cook 30 minutes more.

title: pinto bean and rice casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine beans, picante, rice, beef and 1/2 cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° uncovered for about 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top; melt.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Remove pits and skins from avocados; mash.
In small bowl, mix avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In separate small bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
On large plate, begin layering:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over hot water.
Add chocolate chips and condensed milk.
Heat until blended.
Add marshmallows, chopped pecans, salt and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
This will harden by next day.

title: 20 minute icing
directions: Beat together about 20 minutes.

title: easy slaw
directions: Mix cabbage together well.
Put sugar, vinegar and slaw mix into small bowl and mix well.
Add Mayonnaise and blend
until smooth.
Add to cabbage mix until mixed well.
Let sit in refrigerator for about an hour before serving to blend the flavors.
Keeps at least a week in refrigerator.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Combine cereal and warm water in bowl.
Let stand until water is absorbed.
Combine eggs and sugar in another bowl Beat until well blended, using mixer at medium speed.
Beat in syrup, butter, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Stir in cereal mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until top of pie is puffy and golden brown.

title: golden baked peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove seeds from peppers; parboil 5 minutes.
Drain.
Heat cheese spread in saucepan over low heat; stir in corn and tomato.
Fill peppers.
Top with crumbs tossed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch
casserole dish.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and place over broccoli.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Combine cake mix with applesauce, eggs and orange and lemon flavorings.
Mix well. Toss cherries, pineapple, dates and pecans with flour to coat well. Stir fruit and nuts into cake mixture, mixing well.
Pour mixture into 2 loaf pans that are greased and floured.
Bake at 275° for 1 3/4 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: apple cake
directions: Put in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Layer 2 cups crushed pretzels and margarine.
Cut up on top of pretzels.
Set in warm oven approximately 10 minutes, long enough to melt butter.
Take out of oven and let cool.

title: japanese ham-fried rice
directions: Heat the 2 tablespoons of peanut oil in wok over a high heat. Lightly beat the eggs and slowly pour into the hot oil.
Swirl the wok until the eggs set, then remove the solid egg mass and lay out on a chopping block over toweling.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Stir butter into boiling water.
Stir until melted.
Beat in powdered sugar, milk and salt.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into squares. Makes 3 dozen (1-inch) pieces.

title: caramels
directions: Do not try this recipe when humidity is high.
Caramels may not get firm.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine and maple flavoring. Beat in the egg whites, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to egg mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cook and cut.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello into cottage cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and whipped topping.
Mix well.
Place in bowl and chill overnight.

title: white christmas fudge
directions: *Three cups in all of nuts.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan or a 10-inch iron skillet.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal.
In a medium size bowl, beat eggs with a fork just enough to blend yolks and whites.
Stir in milk and oil with egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients and stir to blend thoroughly.
Beat just until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and bake about 25 minutes.

title: chicken brunch bake
directions: Combine bread and broth. Add chicken, rice, peppers, parsley and salt. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking dish. Pour eggs over all. Bake uncovered at 324 ° for 1 hr. Serves 8.

title: date and nut squares
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan; melt in pan on low heat sugar and margarine until melted.
Beat in flour, soda, dates, nuts and eggs; spread in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup(low-fat)
directions: In 2 1/2-quart saucepan, saute onion and celery in 3 tablespoons of the chicken broth.
Add broccoli and cover; cook about 5 minutes.
Blend cottage cheese and milk in blender until smooth.
Mix cornstarch with remaining chicken broth and add to broccoli mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and stir in cheese mixture.
Heat through, but do not boil. Makes 6 servings at 1.18 g of fat per serving.

title: black-eyed peas rice
directions: Fry salt pork in Dutch oven to render fat.
Remove pork from fat with spoon.
Add water and black-eyed peas.
Cover and cook over low heat.
After 1 hour of cooking, test peas for taste and add salt if needed.
When peas are tender, add rice.
Cover and simmer until water is absorbed.

title: fresh fruit glaze
directions: Boil until thickened.
Add Tang, if you wish.
Two batches of this makes enough for a 13-quart mixing bowl.
Peach juice can also be added.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Add coconut and vanilla (reserve enough coconut for meringue).
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with stiffly beaten egg whites and coconut.
Brown in oven at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Cook black beans.
Let cool.
Mix chopped tomato, cilantro leaves, scallions, salsa, corn kernels and sour cream.
Pour into black beans.
Chill and serve.

title: kid kake
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces and separate into two bowls.
Sprinkle 1/2 package strawberry jello over one bowl of cake and toss to mix.
Do the same with the other bowl of cake using 1/2 package raspberry jello.
Add 1 cup sugar to sliced strawberries.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to blueberries.
Layer strawberry jello/cake mixture, strawberries and spread a layer of Cool Whip over this.
Continue layering with other bowl of cake and berries, ending with Cool Whip.
Stir gently to mix.
Cover and let chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs and mix in oatmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chocolate chips.
Add pecans and Hershey bar.
Form golf ball size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain mixed vegetables. Mix all ingredients except for crackers. Pour into a baking dish and top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: b.l.t. dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add chopped tomato.
Cook bacon until extra crispy.
Crumble and add to mixture.
Stir.
Chill well.
Serve with toasted bread cut into triangles for dipping.

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice Italian bread into 3/4-inch slices.
Spread each slice with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle each slice with garlic powder. Toast in toaster oven until crispy and bubbly.
Enjoy.

title: zucchini drops
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Dip zucchini into mixture.
Combine all other ingredients.
Put moistened zucchini in bowl and roll until coated thoroughly.
Fry in cooking oil in skillet.
Brown on both sides.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Heat water and salt in 4-quart pan on high until boiling.
Add potatoes.
Cover and cook until done. Drain and mash.
Add butter, cream cheese, chives, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth; gradually add milk to make potatoes creamy and fluffy.
Refrigerate in covered container.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
When ready to cook, put in greased glass dish.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Chop lettuce and spread across cookie sheet.
Chop celery and onion and sprinkle across top of lettuce.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Spread across top of salad. Finish by sprinkling Bac*Os on top.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: shamrock delight
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in saucepan.
Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Stir in milk.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Stir in jelly until melted. Remove from heat and stir in mint extract and coloring.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg white in large bowl until stiff peaks form. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold topping into gelatin mixture, then fold cake meringue.
Turn into 12-cup mold.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold and serve.

title: vermicelli with herb meat sauce
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown meat and drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir often.

title: sugar cookies with raisin filling
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix in flour.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll small portions at a time on a floured board.
Make a round ball and flatten.
Fill with Raisin Filling, cover with another cookie and press edges together with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until well coated.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake sheet cake via directions on box (substitute milk). Remove from oven and poke holes in cake.
Add Eagle Brand milk. Wait 10 minutes.
Pour coco mix over cake.
Let cool and add Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: salmon soup
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in large kettle.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Skim foam.
Reduce to simmer and cook approximately 1/2 hour until fish is very tender.
Strain through colander, saving fish stock.
Cook fresh vegetables in water until just tender.
Drain.
Return fish stock to kettle.
Add half and half and heat to boiling.
Add vegetables and chunked salmon that was cooked in stock.
(Discard heads, skin and bones.) Season to taste.
Serve with pat of butter and chopped fresh dill.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 1/4-inch circles.
Cook carrots until barely tender; drain and set aside.
Heat together soup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Pour hot mixture over carrots.
Add onion, pepper and celery and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before using if possible.
Keeps well in airtight container in refrigerator, 1 to 2 weeks.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix the bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, pepper and salt together.
Melt margarine in pan.
Add garlic powder.
Dip chicken pieces into margarine, then roll into bread crumb mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In large skillet melt butter.
Add mushrooms and onions; saute until onion is tender (about 3 minutes).
Add soup and cheeses; stir until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli, almonds, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Pour into crock-pot; keep hot until serving.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Over medium heat, cook the sugar, milk and chocolate until it reaches soft ball stage.
Add the peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla; beat (with a spoon) until thick and smooth.
Spread into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Melt the margarine in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Add the squash and onion; cook for about 8 minutes or until tender. Stir in the parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano. Combine the eggs and cheese in a large bowl; mix well. Stir in the cooked vegetable mixture. Separate the crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place in an ungreased 10-inch pie plate, 12X8-inch baking dish or 11-inch quiche dish; press over the bottom and up the sides to form a crust. firmly press the perforations together to seal. Spread the mustard over the crust (do not spread mustard to the top of the crust) and evenly pour the egg mixture. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. If necessary, cover the crust with foil during the last 10 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning. Let the pie stand for 10 minutes before serving. If a 12X8-inch baking dish is used, unroll and separate the dough into 2 long rectangles; press over the bottom and 1 inch up the sides to form the crust. Firmly press the perforations together to seal. Continue as directed above.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Should be firm in the center when done.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine milk and meat.
Divide in 5 balls.
On waxed paper, pat each to a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each.
Draw meat over stuffing.
Seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Stir in milk.
Let thicken slightly. Add cream cheese.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.
Layer in dish, broccoli and potatoes.
Put cheese on top.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: purple cow shakes
directions: Put ingredients in blender on high for 30 seconds.
Enjoy right away.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar. Mix until cinnamon is well blended.
Add eggs, salad oil, carrots, pineapple and pecans.
Mix on medium speed until batter is smooth and silky.
Pour batter into two 9-inch layer pans that have been lined with wax paper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool, then ice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix well and place in buttered 1 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill an 8-inch pie pan with apples. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix butter, salt, sugar, flour, egg and nuts together.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: carob chip cookies
directions: In a blender, put the water, vanilla, walnuts and dates. First allow the dates to soften in the water.
In a bowl, place all other ingredients.
Blend ingredients in blender until smooth and add to dry ingredients in bowl and mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dinner slaw
directions: Mix salad dressing, vinegar, Wesson oil and sugar until sugar is mixed good, so it won't lump. Add cabbage, onion, carrots and sweet pepper. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: confetti spring salad
directions: Place the corn, peas, celery, onion, green pepper and pimiento in a bowl.
Mix the Italian dressing and sugar and add to vegetables.
Chill.

title: polka dot potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, soup, onion, green pepper and salt in a small saucepan.
Simmer over low heat until slightly thick.
Put potatoes and vegetables into a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix apples, pineapple and peanuts together.
Pour dressing over and stir gently.
Garnish top with additional pecans.
Yields 10 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cool for 4 hours and serve.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine
sugar and spices in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix well; add
beans,
egg
yolks and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Pour
into a	pastry	shell.	Bake
at
350°	for 15 minutes. Reduce	heat to	300°; bake for 45 minutes.
Make meringue of egg
whites and 6 tablespoons of sugar;
spread on top of pie. Brown for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti for sixteen
directions: Heat chicken broth and saute onion and green peppers until tender. Boil spaghetti and rinse. Combine spaghetti, onion, peppers, tomatoes, mushrooms, soup and diced chicken. Mix well. Add grated cheese. May season as desired with black pepper, garlic powder and a little red pepper for just a bit of tang. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "mock pot roast" dinner
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in order.
Cover tightly with foil.
Do not uncover.
Bake at 350° for exactly 2 1/3 hours. Remove from oven and let set, covered, for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: puppy chow snack
directions: Melt together
chocolate chips, oleo and peanut butter. Pour this
mixture
over
Rice
Chex.
Stir until coated well, then put in
brown
grocery bag and cover with powdered sugar. Shake until covered with sugar.
Keep in covered containers in freezer.

title: broccoli and pasta
directions: Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
Steam with carrots until tender; set aside.
Cook pasta.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt margarine and caramels; mix well.
Stir in condensed milk.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over baked cake.
Pour caramel mixture over all. Pour remaining cake batter over caramel and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon wow bars
directions: Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar together.
Like a pie crust, spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Mix eggs, sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Pour over the hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: finger rolls filled with linguica spread
directions: Remove casing from linguica and grind all ingredients (except finger rolls) and blend with fork.
Cook a day or two ahead.

title: the thing cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, pecans and 1 egg.
Pat this thick mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs and pour this mixture on top of first layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix together in microwavable dish for 4 minutes on High; stir. Microwave 4 minutes again.
Garnish with sliced olives.
Use plain Doritos as dippers.
(Served at the '94 Jump Crew Dinner.)

title: chocolate snappers
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. In large bowl, combine shortening, sugar and egg; beat until creamy.
Mix in corn syrup and Choco Bake.
Now blend in mixture that is in small bowl.
Shape into small balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange au lait cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs singly, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine yogurt and baking soda.
Add alternately with flour.
Beat in orange juice and rind.
Pour into well-buttered Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack; dust with powdered sugar.
Decorate with fresh strawberries and mandarin orange slices (optional).

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let the flavors blend a few hours in the refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great no-fat dip!

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and mix sugar and vanilla well.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: pat-in-the-pan pie crust
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter with a fork or pastry blender.
Whe dough resembles pebbles, then press into pie plate. Bake at 400° up to 15 minutes, until crust is lightly golden.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, butter and spices.
Add sweet potatoes; beat and add undiluted Pet milk.
Beat again thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and finish baking.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, Pet milk and salt 8 minutes; turn off heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Melt and pour into buttered pan.
Do not beat.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a plastic bag; shake well.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; dip chicken pieces in melted margarine. Shake a few at a time in bread crumb mixture.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: favorite green bean casserole
directions: Simmer beans 15 minutes, then drain well. Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Top with pinch of paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: diet banana nut bread
directions: Mash overripe bananas.
Add NutraSweet and butter.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Spray loaf pan with Pam and pour in batter.
Bake in a 325° oven.
Sweet 'N Low does not work as well as NutraSweet.
I use Weight Watchers butter.

title: lifeway pecan toffee treats
directions: Line cookie sheet (11 x 15 with sides) with foil.
Completely fill cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Mix butter and sugar. Stir constantly as you cook.
Bring to full, rolling boil and TIME for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread to edges.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup chopped pecans.
Bake 12 minutes in preheated oven at 325°.
Remove from oven and let set 1 minute.
Remove with spatula and place on waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Add noodles and stir.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: dill dip for veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients; let sit in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Serve with any dipping veggie and enjoy!

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and mix alternating with milk to cream mixture.
Add lemon extract. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare 6 bell peppers, cutting off top and seeding; parboil for 3 minutes.
Drain.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1 cup warm water; let sit about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar, salt, margarine and shortening in a large bowl; add boiling water, stirring until margarine and shortening melt.
Cool slightly.
Add dissolved yeast, stirring well.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour, beating until smooth.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough; put in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top of dough.

title: hard crust pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour a large tube pan.
In a large mixing bowl, cream Crisco and sugar together.
Then add flour and eggs alternately.
Mix well after each addition.
Add Pet milk and flavorings.
Beat well.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours.
This makes a very large cake.

title: granola
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over oats mixture; mix well.
Pour into large pan so it can be spread rather thin.
Bake in a 325° oven until lightly toasted.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: potato delight
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix together with other ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: butter brickle dessert
directions: Butter pan.
Pour in peaches and juice.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Dribble oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients except chocolate chips together in a bowl. Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips on top.
Do not stir!
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix with peanut butter and sugar. Stir in Rice Krispies.
Form into balls using a melon baller. Melt chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Drop the balls into chocolate; roll, then lift out with a fork and place on a cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Put in freezer for 5 minutes. Remove balls from cookie sheet and store in covered tins in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: You can do almost anything with fruits.
Just add sugar to taste and mix.
Combine with whipped cream, yogurt or mayonnaise or a blend of all three.
Punch bowl on ice and serve in punch bowl cups.

title: reese's yummy pieces delicious peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together butter and peanut butter.
Work together thoroughly, except for chocolate chips.
Press evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Melt over hot water.
Spread melted chips quickly and evenly over peanut butter mixture and refrigerate thoroughly before cutting.

title: pound cake, golden
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: potato and herb soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add potatoes. Cover and let stand 5 minutes to allow potatoes to absorb butter.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine in 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour in melted margarine and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until middle is done.

title: grandma root's homemade buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and make pancakes!!! Blueberries or any fruit can be added. Very good and so easy to make.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Combine veggies, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until veggies are done. Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in rows on top.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry french toast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Diagonally cut bread into 1-inch slices and place in dish.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in milk until well blended.
Pour mixture over bread, turning slices to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: meat sauce for pasta
directions: In a dutch oven, cook meat and onion over medium heat until met is no longer pink. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, mushrooms, parsley and seasoning. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes stirring occasionally. Uncover, simmer 15 minutes longer or until sauce reaches desired consistency. Discard bay leaves.

title: richmond chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add chocolate and salt.
Add water. Cook until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Spread on cake while hot for a glossy frosting which remains soft and smooth.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil together sugar, flour, water and vinegar.
Stir and cool.
When cool, mix in mayo and mustard.
Stir macaroni, celery, onion, eggs, carrots, parsley, salt and pepper together.
Mix well.
Pour dressing over macaroni and stir until coated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in bottom of casserole dish. Mix the rest of the ingredients except stuffing in a separate bowl.
Put on top of broccoli. Sprinkle stuffing on top and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Place
steak
in crock-pot or slow cooker.
Add soup and onion dip mix.
Cook on low heat for about 8 to 10 hours.

title: jacob wirth's sauerbraten
directions: Rub meat with salt and ginger; put in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except oil and flour.
Bring to a boil and pour over meat.
Cool, cover and put in refrigerator for 3 days. Turn meat once each day.
Remove meat from pickling liquid and reserve liquid.
Brown meat on all sides in oil.
Place on rack. Add pickling liquid, onions and pickling spice.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 hours or cook in pressure cooker 12 minutes per pound.
Remove meat.
Strain liquid in pan and return to heat.
Skim off excess fat.
Thicken gravy with crumbled gingersnaps and a little flour thickened with cold water.
Peel and cut up potatoes, carrots and turnip.
Cook for 10 minutes in pressure cooker and serve with meat and gravy.

title: orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until tender, about 1 hour.
Add mandarin oranges and baste with liquid during last 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry hamburger; add salt and pepper.
Add a can of ripe olives to hamburger.
Heat; stir in saucepan, enchilada sauce, tomato soup, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Lay tortilla flat in baking pan.
Put hamburger mixture in each tortilla and roll the tortilla.
Pour enchilada sauce over tortillas in baking pan.
Use enough sauce to cover the enchiladas.
Sprinkle grated cheese over enchiladas.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with chopped onion and lettuce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain off part of the juice.
Mix the dry vanilla pudding with the fruit.
Chill.

title: golden party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 6 cups water in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients except 7-Up in blender container and process until smooth.
Combine with sugar syrup in large container, mixing well. Freeze until slushy.
Mix equal part punch mixture and 7-Up in punch bowl.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: pineapple sheet pie
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add water until flour is moistened.
Gather into 2 balls.
Roll one and put on cookie sheet.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and milk.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish. Put chicken on top of it, skin side down.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 250° oven, uncovered, and cook for 3 hours. Turn once during cooking.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Mix sugar, marshmallow cream, Pet milk and butter in heavy pan on medium heat.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chips and Heath bars.
Beat until chips melt.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: ranch beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large roasting pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot shortening.
Blend in flour.
Add soups, water, onion and spices.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Cook in oven for 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.
I use this recipe in my crock-pot.
It's also very good warmed up.
Enjoy!

title: more please
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onions and celery. Cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except noodles. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, stirring once or twice during baking.
Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve as a dip with tortilla chips or use as a topping for rice, beans, etc.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, until heated through and bubbly.
May be frozen.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Mix next 3 ingredients together, add together.
Stir in 3 c. rolled oats. Shape into 2 logs about 5 x 2 1/2 inches thick.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice thin (1/8 inch) using a sharp knife. Place on cookie sheet, lightly greased.
Bake 8 minutes (time may vary) at 400°.

title: varsity chowder
directions: Mix potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and salt and pepper in a saucepan; add boiling water.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender; do not drain.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a large skillet, with bacon grease, cut up several yellow squash and zucchini squash, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook this until it is tender.
Add a little garlic powder.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut half the cake into chunks or crumble into bottom of a 3-quart bowl.
(This is traditionally served in a clear glass bowl so the layers are visible.)
Sprinkle with half of the sherry. Top with half the custard, half the raspberry jam, then half the cream and half the almonds.
Refrigerate at least 2 to 4 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add vegetables (as many as you want), bacon bits (as much as you want), 1 small or 1/2 large bottle creamy Italian dressing.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, add remaining dressing.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges together.
Add crushed pineapple and sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Pound veal and dredge with mixture of salt, pepper and flour. Saute both sides in butter and olive oil until golden brown.
Add parsley and garlic.
Add bouillon, sherry and mushrooms.
Simmer until meat is tender (about 30 minutes).

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Put apples in 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar and spices. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until apples are soft. Cream butter. Gradually add granulated sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg and beat well. Add sifted ingredients, alternating with milk, beating until smooth. Spread on cooked apples. Bake for 30 minutes. Serve warm with cream or low-fat Cool Whip. Makes 4 servings.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Saute onion in skillet with small amount of oil.
Add beef and brown over medium heat.
Drain grease from mixture.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, spaghetti sauce mix and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Cook noodles according to directions on package. Layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, beginning and ending with noodles, cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a serving bowl, arrange cucumber, onion and red or green chili in layers.
Mix sugar, salt and vinegar; add hot water and stir until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, water, pudding and melted chocolate. Beat 2 minutes, then mix in sour cream. Add chips and nuts. Bake in Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: pringles
directions: Cook all ingredients (except pecans) in a large pot to soft boil stage.
When it is done, add 2 cups of broken pecans.
Beat until it gets thick.
Drop in mounds on wax paper.
If it is too thick, add a few drops of boiling water.

title: chicken noodle dish
directions: Bake chicken breasts, covered with foil for 30 minutes at 400°. Add both soups and cook for additional 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed and serve chicken over cooked noodles as a main dish.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salted water until tender. While chicken cooks, mix chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and green pepper in a large bowl.
Remove chicken from broth. Skin and bone. Tear tortillas in 4 pieces and dip in broth.
Line casserole dish with tortillas, then layer chicken, sauce and cheese. Repeat tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheese until all sauce is used.
Top with cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat
until
sugar
dissolves.	Boil 1 minute; remove from heat and beat until it is spreading consistency.

title: freezer corn
directions: Mix water, margarine, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn and cook for 20 minutes.
Add more hot water if needed. Chill and freeze.
Ready to eat.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Toast nuts for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Chop fruit and add nuts.
Pour into cracker crumbs.
Melt marshmallows and milk in microwave.
Stir into cracker mix and press down firmly into container.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Freeze the marshmallows.
Melt in a double boiler the margarine, Eagle Brand milk and caramels.
Dip frozen marshmallows in mixture; roll in Rice Krispies and chopped pecans.

title: spanish rice
directions: Put uncooked rice in casserole and pour boiling water over it. Add butter, tomatoes, hamburger, onions, pepper, salt and green peppers.
Bake 1 hour or more at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: greta's fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken, then add salt.
Mix flour and meal; sift together.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Fill frying pan 1/3 full of vegetable oil.
Heat oil until hot.
Put chicken in oil.
Cover and brown.
Turn chicken until all sides are brown.
Turn heat down to a slow simmer for about 25 minutes.
Keep turning chicken; this lets chicken get tender.

title: grape-blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Pour juice from pineapple into cup.
Add enough water to make 1 full cup; add this to the jello and boiling water.
Stir until jello is completely dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and blueberry pie mix.
Refrigerate until moderately set.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Prepare sauce in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray, cook onion and celery until tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, oregano and garlic over high heat to bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: party punch(serves 50)
directions: Boil sugar and water in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in orange juice concentrate, cranberry juice and pineapple juice.
Chill until serving time. Combine with lemon-lime soda in punch bowl at serving time.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 to 9 servings.

title: gingerbread carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix gingerbread mix, water and egg in medium bowl with a fork about 2 minutes until batter is uniform in color and consistency.
Stir in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese in a medium bowl on low speed until smooth.
Beat in whipped topping until mixture is smooth and spreadable.
Frost cake with cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining cake.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: cinnamon tea
directions: Mix water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves; boil for 5 minutes. Add tea bags for 5 minutes.
Add juices and boil 10 minutes more.

title: "cream of wheat" cornbread
directions: Mix well first 6 ingredients.
Pour in remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased iron skillet and bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: mustard salad dressing
directions: In a double boiler mix sugar, flour, mustard and butter.
Add egg, milk and vinegar.
Cook until thickened.

title: cedrick's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter and add ground beef; season lightly and brown.
Place 4 cups cabbage in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat, then add 3 cups chopped cabbage.
Pour 10 1/2 ounce can tomato soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Spread lettuce over bottom of large bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan. Add remaining ingredients, layering in order.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
Just before serving, add tomatoes.

title: tom's onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat and saute the onions until clear and tender. Butter a 2-quart 8 x 11 x 2-inch casserole. Reserve 3 tablespoons cracker crumbs for topping and line dish with remaining crumbs.

Add onions and soup in alternate layers until dish is full. Cover the top with the beaten eggs and pour milk over the top. Sprinkle grated cheese and reserved cracker crumbs over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
An excellent recipe.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix sugar with eggs, then stir in oil and biscuit mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in oblong pan at 325°
for 45 minutes.
Middle of cake will fall when almost done.
Cool, cut in squares to serve.

title: breakfast souffle(serves 12)
directions: Butter and cut crusts off bread.
Cut in 1-inch squares. Place 1/2 of bread cubes in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Shred Cheddar or Jack cheese and place 1/2 of the cheese on bread cubes. Dice 1 1/2 slices of ham, about 1/2-inch thick, or have butcher dice about 2 cups.
Place on top of shredded cheese.
Place other 1/2 of bread crumbs over that.
Top with last 1/2 of shredded cheese.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid; add water, if necessary, to equal 1/2 cup liquid.
Bone and finely flake salmon; set aside. Sprinkle gelatin over reserved salmon liquid.
Place over hot water and stir to dissolve.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve first 4 ingredients and let chill until firm.
Whip in lemon pie filling and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Stir 1/2 of the whipped topping into remaining gelatin with wire whisk until blended.
Pour into 8-inch square dish.
Refrigerate about 10 minutes until set but not firm.
Carefully spoon fruited gelatin over creamy layer in dish.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into squares.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Makes 9 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
May be made early.
Serve with crackers.

title: plain cake
directions: Blend Crisco with sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Peel and core fruits.
Coarsely grind or chop fruit.
Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Pack hot in sterilized jars and seal.

title: pineapple-cheese cake dessert
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions; cool.

title: garlic soup(serves 4)
directions: Mince garlic and saute in oil until golden brown (do not burn). Remove garlic and discard, then saute bread. Add broth and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Add eggs very slowly to broth, trying not to curdle them. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with a lime wedge.

title: the best chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until creamed.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and M&M's.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes; cookies will look moist.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple. Mix flour and sugar. Add drained pineapple. Gently stir thoroughly. Pour into buttered glass loaf pan. Mix the cracker crumbs with melted butter and cover the top of the casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat.
Stir in water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In salad bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except chips.
Toss well.
Place lettuce mixture on salad plates.
Spoon on meat.
Top with corn chips. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
In small bowl, mix grated cheese and cream cheese until well blended.
Mix in deviled ham. Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into a ball or 2 (8-inch) logs. Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with rye bread or crackers.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Add cream cheese and melt.
Add crabmeat.
Season to taste with all seasonings.
Keep heated in crock-pot or chafing dish.
Serve with Wheat Thins or other favorite crackers.

title: lite microwave garden club meat loaf
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into well and over remainder.
Cook on 80% power 10 minutes.
Rotate after 5 minutes, if no turntable. Cook on High, 5 to 7 minutes.
Check center for doneness.
Let sit for 10 minutes.

title: apple and onion stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Saute until tender. Remove from heat and sprinkle spices and broth mix over onion mixture.
Stir to blend. Add apple and bread cubes. Toss stuffing, adding water gradually until bread is just moistened. Add more water, if a moister stuffing is desired.
Place in a lightly oiled 1-quart baking dish. Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: velveeta hot dish
directions: In large casserole, combine browned hamburger, noodles, green pepper, onions, soups and cheese.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: uncooked vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Freeze according to freezer instructions in 1 1/2 gallon freezer.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Cut in 1 cup margarine until mixture comes to resemble coarse crumbs. Sprinkle in pan and press firmly. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cajun hot wings
directions: In saucepan, bring hot sauce and butter to a boil.
With pair of tongs, dip each piece of chicken in hot sauce mixture and then arrange on baking tray.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Take tray out of oven.
Pour off all grease.
Again, dip each piece of chicken in the remainder of the sauce mixture.
Bake for another 30 minutes at 400°.
Take off baking tray immediately and place on serving dish.
If any sauce mixture is left it could be used for dipping on the table.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: For cooking liquid, in a bowl, combine cola, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, garlic, bouillon granules, mustard, chili powder and red pepper.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid for sauce.

title: applesauce cake(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and cloves.
Beat together on medium-high speed for 1 1/2 minutes the shortening, sugar and 2 unbeaten eggs.
Add the applesauce, raisins, nuts and the sifted flour mixture.
Beat on medium speed about 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans and bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: coeur a la creme
directions: Mix cheese and cream until smooth; add sugar and sherry. Dissolve jello in cold water.
Heat coffee cream; add jello and mix well.
Mold and top with strawberries.

title: steak tetrazzini
directions: Cut steak into strips, brown in frying pan.
Place in medium roaster pan.
Add onion, pepper and mushroom slices.
Pour spaghetti sauce over these ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Melt cheese on top.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: curried chutney dip
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together well in a food processor and chill.
Serve with crackers or use as a spread on dates or celery.

title: mexican bites
directions: Mix and spread on tortillas. Roll up. Wrap in Saran Wrap; twist the ends. Refrigerate 2 hours. Slice and serve.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle a little grated cheese over top so that it browns nicely.
Bake in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(I usually triple the recipe.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chip n' cherry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour.
Measure flour and remaining dry ingredients.
Sift half the dry ingredients into the mixture and beat.
Sift remaining dry ingredients into mixture and stir until blended.
Add both chips, raisins and diced cherries; stir.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add sugar to stiffly beaten egg whites and beat until mixture stands in soft peak.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and shortening.
Pour into flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Use 1/2 cup batter for each waffle.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients by hand.
Put nuts and vanilla in last.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cake should look like it isn't finished baking. Remove from oven and spread marshmallows over top of cake.
Put back in oven at 350° until marshmallows soften and puff up.
Don't let them get too brown.
This should take about 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool 1 hour, then put icing on cake.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients, about 4 minutes, on medium speed. Make 3 layers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: hershey almond pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in microwave.
Add almond Hershey bars to mixture and stir to melt candy.
Let cool completely.
Add Cool Whip and pour in crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.
Grate plain Hershey bar over Cool Whip.
Chocolate lover's delight!

title: butter banana nut cake
directions: Bake according to directions on cake mix box less 1/4 cup water.
Let cool completely and cover with Banana Cream Cheese Icing.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus in baking dish. Layer sliced eggs. Layer cheese. Make layers until all things are used up. Top with cheese. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl mix sugar and flour.
In saucepan combine and let come to a boil the water, margarine, Crisco and cocoa.
Mix flour mixture and hot mixture together.
Then add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into 15-1/2x10-1/2x1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tests done.
Frost while warm with the following:

title: seafoam candy
directions: Heat brown sugar, water and vinegar gradually to a boiling point.
Only stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, without stirring, until mixture forms a hard ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat and when syrup stops boiling, pour slowly into the egg whites.
Add vanilla and beat until it stands up in little peaks when dropped on a buttered dish.

title: chicken italian
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onions and mushrooms over chicken.
Pour sauce over all.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve with pasta or rice.

title: broiled fish
directions: Roll as much as you will need of Pepperidge Farm stuffing. Roll fish into dressing until well covered.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash and lemon seasoning.
Top each piece with some margarine.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn after half done.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Blend together and cook in top of double boiler for 15 to 20 minutes or until thick.

title: indian pudding
directions: Bring milk to just before a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl, then add with whisk to milk.
Bring to boil and add butter.
Stir constantly.
Pour in 1 to 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour, stirring several times.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Pare watermelon rind, removing green and pink portion.
Cut rind into 1-inch pieces.
Dissolve salt in water, add rind and let stand 6 hours or overnight.
Drain, rinse and cover with cold water in large saucepot.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and set aside.

title: potato quiche
directions: Rub small amount of margarine over bottom and sides of 8-inch glass pie plate.
Combine potatoes and onion; pat into pie plate to form quiche crust.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Combine egg, milk, parsley, paprika, dry mustard and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top of quiche.
Microwave at Medium-high for 7 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 as a side dish.
Calories:

title: crab au gratin
directions: Stir together butter and flour over medium heat; add milk. Stir until slightly thick.
Take off heat and add egg yolk, salt and pepper.
Heat and stir continuously.
As it thickens, add cheese, the sherry and crabmeat.
Put into shells; sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Heat in hot oven until bubbly and brown on top.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, beating after each one, and Hershey syrup.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake on cookie sheet, depending on how thick you want them.
(No baking powder or soda.)
Bake 30 minutes.

title: heath candy bar cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and oleo to consistency of pie crust. Reserve 1 cup for the topping and add eggs, milk and baking powder to the rest of the mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle on the topping and 6 crushed Heath candy bars. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: yum-yum cake(fruit cake without the fruit)
directions: Cook the raisins in the water for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a Bundt or angel food cake pan and bake for 1/2 hour at 350° and then at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; add oleo, 1/2 cup bananas and the eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Add 1 cup bananas and vanilla; beat 1 minute longer.
Bake in 3 or 4 layers at 375° until done.
Cool layers.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Pour hot water over raisins and let stand.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add the pork and beans to this mixture and beat well. Combine vanilla, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add this to first mixture and beat well.
Now add the cups of flour and beat well again.
