Fold in drained raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until well done.

title: round steak barbecue
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Add to steak.
Cover steak and simmer approximately 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.

title: zucchini rice with sausage
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage; push to one side and remove all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add rice, zucchini and onions. Cook and stir until slightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, water, mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Heat just to melt cheese. Enjoy.

title: lightning cheese biscuits
directions: Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer as listed, starting with blueberry pie filling.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: gold coast coffee
directions: Combine coffee, cocoa and milk.
Stir until coffee and cocoa dissolve.
Serve with a small dallop of whipped cream or whipped topping.
Serves 12.

title: paper bag baked ham
directions: Remove skin.
Place whole cloves on top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place in a clean grocer's bag.
Twist end of bag to hold heat.
Place in oven at 350°, fat side up.
Allow 30 minutes per pound of ham.
Do not open oven door until ham is done.

title: 20 minute roll dough
directions: Add eggs, milk, yeast, salt and shortening, then add 2 to 3 cups flour at a time.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Work in pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350°.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Layer potatoes, beef, onions, peppers and tomatoes in a 2-quart casserole. Season each layer with salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with sliced green peppers. Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: For Meat Balls:
Use a 5 pound bag.
Mix ingredients; put all in crock-pot.

title: aunt florie's bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and sugar together. Beat in the eggs.
Sift the flour, soda and salt together.
Stir in the bran flakes and the raisins.
Soak the 100% bran in the cup of boiling water for 1 to 2 minutes, then add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the buttermilk, then the flour and raisin mixture.
Mix thoroughly, then store in the refrigerator in a covered container.
(This mixture will keep 1 to 3 weeks, refrigerated.)
As needed, fill greased pans about 2/3 full.
Bake in the oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add other ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Sift flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt together in bowl.
Add milk and melted butter.
Stir until smooth.
Spread batter over bottom of buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle berries over batter.
Combine water, remaining 1 cup sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until browned.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: butter pecan angel pie
directions: Mix and bake in an oblong dish for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: sara henson's yellow cake layer
directions: Measure and place in a mixing bowl the flour, salt, baking powder, sugar, Crisco and 3/4 cups milk.
Blend for 3 minutes; add eggs and 1/2 cup of milk and vanilla.
Blend 2 more minutes.
Pour into layer cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: elegant fruit pizza
directions: Grease baking sheets.
Cream the Crisco until light and fluffy; beat in sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Stir in milk.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder; stir into creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Split dough in half; shape into 2 balls.
Spread on prepared pizza pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar; let stand 1/2 hour.
Mix shortening and remaining sugar together.
Add salt and egg; mix well.
Add 2 cups lukewarm water and yeast mixture. Stiffen with flour and knead.
Let rise.
Shape into rolls.
Can be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: rhubarb sponge pie
directions: Mix together, adding egg whites last.
Put in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry egg nog punch
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Heat through, but do not boil, stirring constantly.
After taken off the stove, add other ingredients, except ice cream and soda.
Chill egg nog until very cold, preferably the day before you serve it.
When ready to serve, add ice cream and lemon-lime soda to a punch bowl and pour egg nog over it.

title: baked fish with honey mustard
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat a baking dish with oil.
Arrange fillets in dish and fold any thin ends under, so each fillet is an even thickness.
Combine olive oil, lemon juice, honey, mustard, paprika and mayonnaise.
Pour over fish.
Bake 10 minutes or 2 or 3 minutes longer, if fillets are very thick.
Then broil for 2 minutes, until sauce on top is lightly blistered and brown.

title: steak ghengis kahn
directions: Mix cheese, garlic, pepper, salt, soy sauce, coffee, Worcestershire sauce and oil in a blender.
Pour over steak, rubbing marinade in with hands.
Save excess and baste steak while cooking.
Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: * sandra's mess *
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in skillet until pink is gone from meat.
Add tomatoes and as much macaroni as you want.
Add enough water to cover and let simmer until macaroni is done.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: In saucepan, with enough water to cover, heat potatoes and garlic.
Simmer until very tender; drain.
With potato masher, mash potatoes and garlic with milk and salt until smooth.
Stir in parsley; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add other ingredients.
Drop on foil covered cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Place in a 350° oven on second rack from bottom.
Close door; turn oven off.
Leave until cool.

title: excellent vegetable dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together and it is ready to eat.
Double this recipe for a large group.
This is also excellent on baked potatoes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine butter, 1/2 cup sugar with 20 graham crackers. Press into 9x13 pyrex pan. Beat eggs with cream cheese. Add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread over graham crackers. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes then cool. Mix Blueberries, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, and corn starch. Thicken as for pie. Pour over crust. Let stand 5 hours in refrigerator. Top with whipping cream.

title: thai egg rolls
directions: Cook meat in oil until about half done; add salt, pepper, Accent and garlic powder.
Add vegetables and partially cook while constantly stirring.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Stir in the eggs and bean threads.
Drain most of the liquid off.
Mixture is ready to be put in the egg roll shells.
After making the egg rolls, fry in oil.
If desired, these rolls can be frozen and fried later.

title: ring of coconut fudge cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients and pour half of batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Spoon filling on top of batter, then pour remainder of batter over top.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Cool 15 to 25 minutes in pan.

title: rice pudding(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites and egg in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes, stirring after 30 minutes, until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.
Immediately refrigerate any remaining pudding.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Put tomatoes, chiles and garlic in blender.
Blend approximately 10 seconds.
Pour into bowl and add chopped green onions and cilantro.
Stir well and salt to taste.
(For chunkier salsa, chop tomatoes, chile and salsa by hand.)
Make salsa one day in advance for better flavor.
Serve with chips or mix with avocado for easy "guacamole."

title: boneless chicken breasts
directions: Line pan with foil; place chicken breasts in pan.
Add seasoning on chicken; cover with foil.
Put a little water around foil but not on chicken.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour or until tender. Melts in your mouth and low-fat too!

title: hot slaw
directions: Place cabbage in Dutch oven.
Combine egg, sour cream, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir into cabbage.
Cook and stir over medium heat (about 10 minutes) until mixture is hot and creamy.

title: beef and rice surprise
directions: Saute onions and pepper in fat.
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs,
pepper,
onions, salt and 1/2 cup tomato sauce, press into a crust.
Mix cooked rice, remaining tomato sauce and 1/2 cup cheese and spread over beef crust.	Bake in preheated oven for
25 minutes
at 350°.	Add remaining cheese and return to oven to cook 5 more minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute garlic, onion, celery and green pepper in 1 stick margarine.	Cook until soft,
but
not
brown.
Add
2 cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Add cut up chicken to sauce. Salt and pepper to suit taste.
Boil
spaghetti
20	minutes
in broth. Use under chicken sauce or mix together.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add peanut butter.
Pour onto jelly roll pan.

title: slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar and spices until sugar and salt are melted.
While boiling hot, pour over vegetables and set aside to cool.
Use after 3 days.
May be stored in icebox.
Keeps for weeks.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook first four ingredients over low heat.
Boil four minutes. Remove from
heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning packet and tomato sauce to this mixture.
Roll out crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing seams together.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chips over crescent rolls.
Spread ground beef mixture next, then spread layer of sour cream.
Shredded cheese is the last layer.
Sprinkle the remaining cup of tortilla chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: old sage pie
directions: Beat the egg whites stiff, then add the yolk and beat again. Beat in sugar. Then when all is mixed, spread in greased pie plate and bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour. Crust is unnecessary as mixture forms own crust. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: pineapple sandwiches
directions: Mix and spread on bread.

title: turkey goulash, austrian style
directions: *One cup of prepared chicken or turkey broth may be substituted for bouillon and water.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Crumble bread and soak in milk.
Mix all together and make into thick patties.
Brown on all sides.
Add a "tiny bit" of water and simmer.
Make gravy and pour over steaks.
Can be made and put in gravy in oven to finish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish except about 1/3 of the noodles.
Sprinkle the remaining noodles over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: english monkey
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk. Melt butter, add cheese. Add it to the crumb mixture.
Beat one egg and add to the above with salt and pepper. Cook three minutes in a skillet.
Pour over toast and serve.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add eggplant; stir constantly over medium heat until soft.
Remove from pan.
Add onion and garlic to same pan; saute until clear.
Add eggplant back.
Add tomato paste, salt and pepper and healthy pinches of herbs.
Sprinkle liberally with any kind of wine.
Simmer over low heat; remove from stove and let cool.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate pork chops for 2 hours or overnight (the longer, the better).
Grill or cook on the stove.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Fill pie shell with 1/2 of apples; sprinkle with 1/2 of sugar and cinnamon.
Add remaining apples and sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour, sugar and butter or margarine with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples. Bake at 450° for ten minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin tins.
Soak oats in milk for 15 minutes.
Add egg, oil, molasses and apples; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to oat mixture.
Stir until just combined.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and bring to
boil.
Set
aside and cool.
Add other ingredients except for
7-Up
or
Sprite. Freeze in 2 one gallon freezer bags.
Remove from freezer 1 to 2
hours before
serving and let it partially
thaw.
Put
in punch bowl and add 7-Up or Sprite.
Serves 50 people.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Work enough flour in to make stiff dough (about 4 cups).
Let rise once and shape into rolls.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix well and freeze in molds.

title: easy cheesy noodle dinner
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; saute onion.
Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in evaporated milk and water.
Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Stir in salt, pepper, noodles, turkey or chicken and peas.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately.

title: lo-cal asparagus soup
directions: Blend together in blender and heat.

title: caramel cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter large spring-form pan.

Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1/3 cup sugar and melted butter. Press into pan, making a little "lip" so caramel does not stick. In a small pan, melt caramels with Eagle Brand milk on low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
In large bowl, combine cream cheese, vanilla, 1 cup sugar and eggs. Beat until smooth.
Pour over caramel/pecan layer.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
(Place foil under cake to catch any butter which may leak.)
Take cake out and turn oven off.
Spread sour cream over cake and return to oven.
Oven remains off! Cool and refrigerate.
Let sit out 1/2 hour before slicing and serving. Very rich!!

title: fruity dip
directions: Stir cream cheese in small bowl until smooth.
Gradually stir in gelatin and milk until well blended.
Chill until ready to serve.
Let stand at room temperature to soften slightly, if necessary.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.
Serve with fruit and cookies.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chinese tuna
directions: Combine all
ingredients and put in casserole.	Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: maxine's chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vinegar, cream and vanilla. Mix only until dissolved.
Bake in pie shell approximately 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tangy chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken breasts in approximately 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Cut diagonally.
Melt butter or margarine in large skillet; add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from skillet, saving the drippings.
Add green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute until tender-crisp.
Return chicken to skillet.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Sprinkle your chicken with lemon juice.
Crumble 6 bouillon cubes evenly over the chicken.
Cook until done at 350°.

title: cherry delights
directions: Put a vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner.
Mix eggs, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla on medium
speed for 5 minutes.
Spoon cupcake liner 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: summer tomato salad
directions: Layer tomato and cheese slices in a shallow dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 basil and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup Tarragon Vinaigrette.
Top with cucumber and onion slices. Sprinkle with remaining basil, pepper and dressing.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla, cocoa and boiling water in an ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Mix brownie mixture as directed on package; spoon mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until firm to touch.
Let cool for 30 minutes; serve warm with fudge sauce which will be in the bottom of the pan.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water with salt until fluffy.
Fry bacon, add vegetables and cook until tender.
Mix with rice, place in casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Soak rind overnight in lime water (2 tablespoons lime to 1 gallon water).
Take out and soak in salt water for 20 minutes. Boil in clear water for 20 minutes.
Boil in mixture of vinegar, sugar and spices until you can stick a fork in the rind.
Put into scalded jars and seal.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease six 6 ounce ramekins (or you can use 6 large crab shells).
Mix bread crumbs and milk in a large bowl. Mix in remaining ingredients gently.
Spoon into shells.
Place shells in jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy; beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use other instructions as modified to these ingredients.
Bake as directed.
Each muffin contains about 200 calories.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cut into small pieces.
Heat soup and water until warm.
Place half of chicken in a baking dish and pour half of the soup mixture over it.
Sprinkle half of the stuffing over this.
Add rest of chicken, other half of soup mixture and rest of stuffing.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 357° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add flour, salt, cream of tartar, soda and egg.
Mix and press in round 14-inch pizza pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients 4 minutes.
Bake in a tube pan 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before frosting.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk and mix.
Sift together and add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Stir in fruit and nuts.
Add juice last.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Combine vinegar, oil, sugar and spices. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Drain when ready to serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Cut bacon into bite size pieces and brown with ground beef and onion.
Do not drain.
Mix beans together (do not drain).
Add beans to the meat mixture.
Stir in catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: stain glass candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large pan.
Stir over medium heat. Heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring, until 310°. Remove from heat.
After boiling stops, add flavoring and color. Pour into a pan of powdered sugar and start snipping into bite-sized pieces.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and butter.
Reserve a small amount for topping.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with remaining crumbs.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip to cheese mixture.
Put cheese mixture over crust.
Spread cherry pie filling over cheese. Sprinkle crumbs and nuts over top.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Yields 15 servings.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook meat until very tender.
Line 9 x 9-inch pan with foil. Place vegetables in pan.
Combine other ingredients (except dressing mix) with stew meat.
Bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Pat down evenly.
Sprinkle dressing mix over mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: sausage loaf - stuffed
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Pull crumbs from each section leaving approximately 1/2-inch crust.
You should have about 3 cups of crumbs.
Brown sausage; drain.
Over low heat, stir in crumbs, beer, spaghetti and tomato sauce.
Stuff bread with meat mixture.
Place loaf together and wrap in foil.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, syrup and melted butter.
Place pecans in bottom of shell and pour mixture over them.
Allow to sit 3 to 5 minutes for pecans to come to the top. (Note:
Be sure all pecans are wet with mixture or they will burn.)
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean.

title: yams
directions: Drain water from the yams.
Cut yams up in about 1-inch chunks.
Mix brown sugar into yams.
Melt butter and pour over yams.
Sprinkle marshmallows over yams.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla together, then add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 50 minutes. Square tin pan is best to use.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put milk in microwavable bowl and cook 2 to 5 minutes on High, until bubbles all.
Remove.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Stir until all melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a foil-lined pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: tacos sealed with refried beans
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion, tomato sauce, garlic salt, chili powder and dash of pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Heat beans and taco shells.
Fill shells with beef, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and seal with beans.

title: e z coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put frozen rolls in bottom of pan. Sprinkle other ingredients over rolls in layers.
Cover loosely with dish towel and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mash the potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with extra cheese.

title: stove top taco casserole
directions: In 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven, brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: deep-pan pizza(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Chop green pepper and onion into small pieces; set aside in a large bowl.
Fry hamburger in Dutch oven.
Drain off grease and place hamburger in bowl with onion and green pepper.
Mix spaghetti sauce with hamburger mixture.
Oil one 8 or 9-inch pie pan with 1 tablespoon oil.
Place tortilla shells in oiled pie pan.
Cover tortillas with hamburger sauce mixture, then top with cheese.
Place in Dutch oven; cook for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening well.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Combine well. Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture, alternating with bananas.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass mixing bowl.
Microwave 7 to 8 minutes.
The mixture will be bubbly. Quickly stir in peanuts, butter and vanilla.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir just until mixture is foamy. Pour immediately onto a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes before breaking into pieces.

title: garden patch salad
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly in a small saucepan. Add 1/2 cup of the water.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1 cup of water and lemon juice.
Chill mixture to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in mixed vegetables. Turn into 3 cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm. Unmold on serving platter and garnish with salad greens, scallions and radishes.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cook beef, green pepper and onion
in a large frypan until brown. Pour off fat.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in rice. Cover and cook over low heat about 25 minutes until rice is tender. Add a little water if needed.

title: mounds bars
directions: Combine butter, graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13 in. pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350 degree oven. Combine coconut and condensed milk and spread over baked crust and bake for another 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Lay unwrapped chocolate bars on top and spread as the chocolate melts.
Cool before cutting.
Tastes like a Mound candy bar.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine beaten sweet potatoes with eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into chilled pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then lower to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat juice from pears and whip softened cheese and jello.
Put pears in blender and whip together.
Let set, then whip Cool Whip and jello mixture together.
Let set.

title: english shepherd pie
directions: Cook and drain hamburg.
Cook potatoes, carrots and onion. When cooked, mash potatoes with butter and milk.
Place half of the sliced carrots and onion in roasting pan on bottom.
Layer hamburg, then potatoes, followed by carrots and onion, then hamburg, then mashed potatoes on top.
Spray with Mazola or Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Arrange alternate layers of shredded cabbage and sliced hard-cooked eggs in greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ono hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and form into patties.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water and honey.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook to 270° to 290° on candy thermometer, soft-crack stage.
Stir in salt, vanilla and desired amount of food coloring.
Pour into well-greased shallow pan.
Let stand until cool enough to handle. Pull portions of candy into rope shapes with buttered hands until light colored and stiff.
Cut into 1-inch pieces with scissors, dipping scissors into cold water frequently.

title: the cake that won't last!
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed according to box.
While cake is baking, mix crushed pineapple with sugar and boil 5 minutes.
When cake is done, punch holes in top and pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Cool cake.
Mix instant pudding as directed and pour over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over pudding.
Place sliced bananas over coconut.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nut meats.
Chill before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana cookies
directions: Combine sugar and margarine. Mix in egg and bananas. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange sour cream loaf(yields 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with mixer on high speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Scrape down sides of bowl and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Then add orange peel.
Scrape bowl again.

title: company chicken
directions: Lightly flour breasts.
Saute in margarine about 20 minutes until brown.
Place ham slice on each breast, a pat of margarine on that and Parmesan cheese on margarine.
Place lid on skillet and steam about 5 minutes.
Take up chicken and place on platter.
Pour wine into drippings.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Pour over chicken.
Serves 6.

title: pwa spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To prepare tea, add 3 heaping teaspoonfuls mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add slightly cooled chocolate, flour,
pecans,	butter	and
vanilla;
beat
well. Spread batter in a	greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Spread frosting evenly over brownies
and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: del sol garden bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute vegetables, onion, mushrooms and garlic in butter for 5 to 7 minutes. Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add ham, cheeses, seasonings and vegetables.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until eggs are puffed and set.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour and oleo until crumbly; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and salt with hands.
If dough is dry, add milk.
Mold dough in pan from 1 teaspoon dough.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Don't make them brown.
Dip in icing.

title: luscious apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots.
Cover with water and boil 20 minutes.
Drain, cool and chop.
Blend butter, granulated sugar and 1/2 cup of the flour until smooth.
Stir in All-Bran.
Spread mixture into bottom of ungreased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: monterey bake
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, milk, salt, green chilies and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese; sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: uncooked cucumber pickle
directions: Pour ice cream salt over cucumbers.
Keep all cucumbers under solution by weighting down with something heavy.
Let set for 14 days.
Remove cucumbers and wash well.
Slice thin or cut as you wish.
Mix one small box of alum dissolved in 1 gal. of water. Let set another 14 days.
pour off alum water and wash again.
Put back into crock, pour 1 gal. apple cider vinegar over slices and let stand 24 hours.
Next morning pour vinegar off and down the drain.
In container put a layer of cucumbers and a layer of sugar.
After sugar has dissolved, put into jars.
Will keep unsealed and unrefrigerated.

title: pizza fondue dip
directions: Combine onion soup, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and oregano in fondue pot.
Heat on range; medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese by handfuls, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Place on fondue stand.
Serve with corn chips.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onion.
Drain one can clams.
Reserve clams and add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Add this to bacon and onions.
Also add diced potatoes and grated carrot.
Add salt and celery salt.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Mix cornstarch with half and half.
Add to soup mixture.
Stir until it thickens a little.
Add clams.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Work in flour and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread evenly in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned around edges.
Cool.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar to softened cream cheese.
Cream well.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix both packages of pudding with 3 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese in pan.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: clam cakes
directions: Grind up common crackers in food processor.
Add clams and eggs.
Mix together.
Add enough evaporated milk to hold cakes together.
Roll in flour.
May be deep fried or fried in pan on top of stove in oil 1/2-inch deep, until golden brown.

title: erin's ricotta cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder (use medium size mixing bowl).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes, drain well and place in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix well; pour into muffin cups and freeze.
Serve on salad plate, garnished with lettuce.
Great for company!

title: curried rice pilaf(yields 6 servings)
directions: In large pot, bring rice to a boil.
In a separate skillet, add oil, onion, corn, peas, bell pepper, celery and curry. Stir-fry until soft, but not browned.
As rice comes to a boil, add ingredients from skillet and red pepper.
Stir.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, brown ground turkey; drain.
Add tomato wedges, tomato sauce and tomato sauce cans filled with water. Bring to a boil; add frozen vegetables and cook until vegetables are done.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Prepare
Rice-A-Roni
and
stuffing
mix
according
to package directions.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, mix both the rice dish and the stuffing.
Stir in the chicken and undiluted soup.
(If the mixture is too dry for your taste, add a little chicken broth).
Heat in a 350° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: senator russell's sweet potatoes
directions: By hand, combine sugar, sweet potatoes, eggs, butter and milk. Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: mexican cheese casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
In a large bowl, combine soup, enchilada sauce, chiles and onion.
Add meat and half of each cheese.
Mix.
Put about 2 tablespoons of the mixture on each tortilla, and roll up tortilla.
Place rolls in large baking dish, putting them close together.
Spread any remaining meat mixture over rolls; sprinkle rolls with other half of each cheese.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts and rolls are hot through.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine flour, salt and cayenne.
Stir in shortening and Cheddar cheese with fork.
Cut into flour mixture. Sprinkle ice water over mixture. When dough forms, divide into thirds and roll onto floured board to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into narrow strips approximately 4 x 1/2-inch (or the size you desire).
Bake in quick 400° oven about 8 or 9 minutes. Watch carefully. Do not scorch.
Remove from oven and place on wire rack to cool.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Layer Tater Tots on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef with the onions until brown; drain the fat.
Layer over Tater Tots.
Mix the soups together; pour over meat mixture evenly.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party punch(beverage)
directions: Soften sherbet and put in a punch bowl. Cut the sherbet into small chunks.
Pour 7-up over the sherbet.
Let set about 5 minutes and stir to mix.
Serve.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Combine warm condensed milk with marshmallows until they are melted.
Add crumbled wafers, raisin and pecans.
Place in buttered pan and press until well packed.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: zesty prune cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat Crisco oil, eggs and sugar until smooth. Combine 2 cups flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with combined buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour, prunes and nuts.
Add to batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Cook cold water and flour until thick and glossy, stirring all the time.
Cool.
Mix together oleo, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add to cooled flour mixture, a little at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: In spite of the name, this cake cannot be inverted onto a platter because the gooey bottom that makes it delicious also makes it stick to the pan.
However, individual pieces can be served upside down.

title: broccoli-tomato salad
directions: Trim ends and leaves from broccoli; peel stem if tough. Slice stem in 1/8-inch diagonal slices. Cut flowerets into bite size pieces. Add tomato, cheese and onions.
Mix gently with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Makes 2 servings.
Double to make more.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and combine pineapple, pears and apricots.
Slice bananas into thawed orange juice.
Combine all of the fruits except the strawberries.
Add sugar and lemon juice to the chopped fruits.
Carefully stir in the thawed strawberries. Yields 25 servings.

title: adirondack camp cookies
directions: In a very large bowl, beat sugars, Crisco, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Gently stir in chocolate chips and coconut.
Using a rounded soup spoon, drop cookies 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brisket roast
directions: Baste meat with ingredients.
Cover and let stand overnight. (Leave covered with foil.)
Cook about 4 hours at 275°.
Remove cover and drain almost all liquid.
Baste with barbecue sauce. Continue cooking uncovered 1 hour.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale or 7-up, chilled, just prior to serving.
Freeze part of punch in a ring mold for icing punch.

title: aunt wilma's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Add chocolate, creme and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is shiny.
Pour out onto buttered trays.

title: quickie caramel rolls
directions: Cut loaf of dough into bite size pieces with sharp scissors or knife.
Arrange in a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix the dry pudding, brown sugar, oleo, milk and cinnamon together and sprinkle over the bread cubes.
If you're using nuts, sprinkle them on top. Cut the second loaf like the first.
Arrange on top of the brown sugar mixture.
Let rise until doubled in bulk and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
To eat, simply pull pieces apart.
Best while still warm.

title: angel dip
directions: Mix well and serve as a dip for apples or other fruit.

title: mom's chicken
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Brown chicken in butter after mixing all dry ingredients.
(You can save dry mixture in a Ziploc bag and store in freezer to use again.)
Remove chicken; place on towels to drain off excess butter.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Melt cheese.
Add 1 heaping spoonful of chili sauce and more cheese.
Bake until golden brown in a 375° oven.
Serves 6.

title: "chewy pecan bars"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 pan with margarine or spray with a nonstick spray.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in a large mixing bowl.	Add in sugar, vanilla and margarine and mix until creamy.
Add flour to mixture and hand mix until blended (batter will be thick).
Mix in pecans.
Spread evenly in prepared pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.	Cool completely and cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix everything together and pour into greased casserole dish. Top with more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Note:
Instead of whipping cream, I have used Cool Whip instead.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until done; mash.
Beat in cream cheese, sour cream, butter and chives.
Add paprika, salt and pepper to taste. Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Dot with additional butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Can be frozen.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: greek salad
directions: Separate
cauliflower, then mix all ingredients together.

title: good salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate until served.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: slushy
directions: Mix well.
Put into wide-mouth container and freeze.

title: german sweet chocolate frosting
directions: Heat margarine, milk and chocolate over low heat until chocolate melts.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in powdered sugar, gradually, beating until smooth.

title: fruit tea
directions: Make tea and add sugar and lemon juice and hot water to make a gallon. Add pineapple juice and stir.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk; boil for 1 minute.
Add oats and peanut butter, mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper while mixture is still hot.

title: chicken pocket
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Add garlic and onion powder to your taste.
Add cream cheese.
Roll out crescent rolls.
Put spoon of mixture on each roll.
Roll over and bake at 350° until brown. Good with salad or soup.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients; roll mixture into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Place on platter covered with powdered sugar and sprinkle sugar over them.

title: crab casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and place crab in it.
Make a white sauce, using the margarine, flour and milk.
Add all spices and pour sauce over crab meat and sprinkle top with the cheese.
Cook in moderate oven for about 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crust: Cream 3/4 cup butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; add 1 1/2 cups flour. Mix thoroughly. Save 1/4 cup crumbs for topping. Press remaining mixture into 2 (8-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 375° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool crust before adding filling.

title: onion-mushroom sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter in a large skillet. Add 1 tablespoon flour and stir until brown. Add water, wine and pepper. Bring to a boil, cooking over low heat, stirring constantly. When smooth and thick, add mushrooms and onions and cook until thoroughly heated. Serve hot over beef patties or steak.
Also good over chicken. Yields about 3 cups.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix well.
Butter loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Fast, easy and delicious.

title: squash pie
directions: Strain squash; add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted in center of custard comes out clean.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Drain in blancher overnight.	The
next
day,
mix
in large pot sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and mustard seed.
Add cucumbers and cook 20 minutes.
Pack
in	hot
jars
and seal.
This is also good in potato salad but I drain it first.

title: garden tomato juice blend
directions: Wash
and drain tomatoes.
Remove core and blossom end. Cut into
quarters.
Simmer
vegetables
minutes.
Press through fine
sieve
or
food
mill.
Season with salt.
Add 2 tablespoons bottled lemon juice or 1/4 teaspoon citric acid to each pint. Bring
juice
blend
to a boil.
Pour hot juice in jars,
leaving 1/4-inch for headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints 40
minutes or quarts 45 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes about 7 quarts.

title: bisquick
directions: Sift into a large bowl.
Mix until it looks like coarse meal. Yields 13 cups.
